le="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Reference: 604 115 213T<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australian Government</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Department of Human Services</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Wendell Nesmith PO Box 99</p><p style="text-align: center;">Canberra ACT 2600</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">4 July 2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Mr Nesmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">Changes to ways you can access our services</p><p style="text-align: center;">I am writing to you following your contact with us at Braddon Service Centre on 4 July 2018.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">During this contact you were disruptive in the Service Centre and refused to leave when directed to do so.</p><p style="text-align: center;">As we discussed on 4 July 2018, this behaviour is not acceptable. You must act with courtesy and respect towards our staff and other customers at all times.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Your service arrangement</p><p style="text-align: center;">As a result of your behaviour on this occasion and to maintain the safety of our staff and customers, I have decided to limit the ways you can access our services.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Your service arrangement will start from 4 July 2018 and end on 10 July 2018. During this period you may only contact us by:</p><p style="text-align: center;">â€¢ calling your One Main Contact, Sam on 02 6211 3490. If Sam is not available, you can call Ashley on 02 6200 5327</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">You may also write, email or fax us. For information about how to do this, please go to</p><p style="text-align: center;">humanservices.gov.au/contact</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">During this period you may not:</p><p style="text-align: center;">â€¢ enter any location delivering Centrelink, Medicare and/or Child Support services</p><p style="text-align: center;">â€¢ use the services of a Departmental Agent or Access Point for Centrelink, Medicare and/or Child Support business.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">If you:</p><p style="text-align: center;">â€¢ attend any of our locations, you will be asked to leave immediately. If you do not leave, we may contact the police.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">For more information</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">fu<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>my.gov.au<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>l!J ExpressPlus mobile apps<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Q<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>humanservices.gov.au</p><p style="text-align: center;">1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">If we need to contact you, we will call or write to you.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">We may provide details of this arrangement to other organisations such as the Department of Employment and the Department of Social Services.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Reviewing your service arrangement</p><p style="text-align: center;">We will review your service arrangement by 10 July 2018 and we may contact you. We may also complete a review if you do not follow this arrangement or if your circumstances change. You can ask us to review your arrangement at any time, however we will only consider reasonable requests.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Â·Â·</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">We will let you know the outcome of any review.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Help with contacting us</p><p style="text-align: center;">If you want someone else to deal with us, you can appoint them to act on your behalf. You can find more information about how to do this by going to humanservices.gov.au/norninees</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">More information</p><p style="text-align: center;">For more information about your responsibilities and our service commitments, please go to</p><p style="text-align: center;">hurnanservices.gov.au/yourresponsibilities</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">If you have any questions about this letter, please call Sam on 02 6211 3490 (call charges may apply). If you are outside the local call area, you can call and reverse the charges.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Yours sincerely</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Service Centre Manager Braddon Service Centre</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">2</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">IN THE AUSTRALIAN CAPITAL TERRITORY CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MH 10812012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In respect of WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH</p><p style="text-align: center;">D.O.B. 2710611984</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Tribunal:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Presidential Member G McCarthy</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Date of Order:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>6 July 2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Whereas -</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(i) The involuntary detention of Wendell Charles Nesmith was authorised at 3:00 pm on 4 July 2018 for a period not exceeding 3 days pursuant to section 85(1) of the Mental Health Act 2015; and</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(ii) The Tribunal has considered an application to extend the period of detention.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ORDER</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">1.Â  The Tribunal orders that the period for which Wendell Charles Nesmith may be detained is extended for a further period not longer than 11 days expiring at 3:00 pm on 18 July 2018.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Note:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 85(4) of the Mental Health Act 2015 entitles a person to apply to the Tribunal for review of Wendell Charles Nesmith's involuntary detention.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 91 of the Mental Health Act 2015 requires the release of Wendell Charles Nesmith as soon as practicable before the period of further detention expires if his detention under section 85 is no longer justified.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">IIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIII</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·1s1s1</p><p style="text-align: center;">ACT Health</p><p style="text-align: center;">Application for a Further Period of Involuntary Detention - not</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Complete details or affix label</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">URN:20163678</p><p style="text-align: center;">Family name:Nesmilh</p><p style="text-align: center;">Given names: Wendell Charles</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">excee â€¢ 1ng 11 d</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ays</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DOB: 27/06/1984<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>