resents as elevated, grandiose, disorganised and poorly kempt. He has significant delusional thought content regarding artificial intelligence, electronic frequencies in his brain and not being human. Mr Nesmith reports that he currently resides in a tent in the bush in Canberra with no permanent address.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Evidence that the person has refused treatment, care or support:</p><p style="text-align: center;">When discussing treatment with Mr NeSmith he stated that all medications make him feel terrible, he does not consent to being ruled by his inferiors and will not take any medications given to him. He has reiterated multiple times that he will not take medication and that he doesn' t believe he needs to be in the unit.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl)</p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl)</p><p style="text-align: center;">C</p><p style="text-align: center;">ca</p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">::::I</p><p style="text-align: center;">0></p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">"O</p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">"i:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl)</p><p style="text-align: center;">a..</p><p style="text-align: center;">I.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl)</p><p style="text-align: center;">.c:</p><p style="text-align: center;">t::</p><p style="text-align: center;">u::::.I</p><p style="text-align: center;">ca</p><p style="text-align: center;">I.</p><p style="text-align: center;">.E</p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">:.;:::;</p><p style="text-align: center;">ca</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·-0 Â­</p><p style="text-align: center;">a.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><(</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Evidence that the detention is necessary for the person's health or safety, social or financial wellbeing, or for the protection of someone else or the public:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In his current mental state, detention is necessary to support Mr NeSmith' s mental</p><p style="text-align: center;">and physical health. His disorganisation means he is at significant risk of harm to himself through misadventure and poor self care. He is a risk to himself financially and reputationally due to his delusional thought content and lack of insight. He is also at risk of harm to and from others as evidenced by the events leading to his presentation</p><p style="text-align: center;">where he was agitated and aggressive in public.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Evidence that adequate treatment care or support cannot be provided in a less restrictive environment:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Given Mr NeSmith' s current mental state and lack of insight, he is quite vulnerable and likely to deteriorate further without ongoing inpatient treatment. He also has no secure accommodation in which further appropriate treatment could be adequately provided.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Signature of Psychiatrist:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Print name: Dr Hassan ,ti.,bass<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Date: 06/07/2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Please give this form to the TRIBUNAL LIAISON OFFICER Fax: 6244 4558 who will forward to ACT CIVIL & ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL Fax: 6205 4855 and</p><p style="text-align: center;">PUBLIC ADVOCATE ACT Fax: 6207 0688</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ACT CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Our Ref:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"