nce is sought to be put before the Court, state briefly the nature of the evidence and what is sought to be proved)</p><p style="text-align: center;">I have both writings and video footage that occurred at and around the time of the order and these are being ignored. In addition, my</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Filed for the appellant Wendell Charles NeSmith, XXXXXX</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">AF2006-388<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Approved form under Court Procedures Act 2004, s 8</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">page 1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">website is being ignored. In addition, my human rights were severely violated when my lawyer quit the last appeal.</p><p style="text-align: center;">5. The grounds of the appeal are:</p><p style="text-align: center;">I was NOT a risk to myself or anyone else at the time the order was made (or at any other time in my life). I was merely protesting one of Centrelink's terrible procedures which I would do again if the same thing happened.</p><p style="text-align: center;">6. The orders sought are:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â  Â  Â  Remove psychiatric order. Bring justice to those who violated my human rights including all of those who chose to ignore real evidence.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if r 5101 (3) applies)</p><p style="text-align: center;">7. *[The appellant wants to present the appellant's case in writing and video.]</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if the appellant is represented by a solicitor)</p><p style="text-align: cente