s NeS</p><p style="text-align: center;">*[swetn/affirmed] on (date).Â  11Â  ;y- r,?A/<...< c+e<..7<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>h- &Pr<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>9</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(The affidavit that you intend to rely on must be filed in the Court with the application (seer 5082).)</p><p style="text-align: center;">(You must, not later than 3 days after the application is filed, serve the following on each person who was a party to, or given leave to intervene in, the proceeding in which the order appealed from was made:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Filed for the applicant by Wendell Charles NeSrnith, XXXXXX:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">AF2006-387<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Approved form under Court Procedures Act 2004, s 8</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">page 1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) a sealed copy of the application;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(b) a stamped copy of the accompanying affidavit;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(c) a stamped copy of the draft notice of appeal (seer 5085).)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Applicant's address for service of documents</p><p style="text-align: center;">(set out applicant's address for service)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">43 Illawarra Court</p><p style="text-align: center;">XXXXXX</p><p style="text-align: center;">Email address: wendell@nesmith.net Date: !0/01/ fl(</p><p style="text-align: center;">Gilb</p><p style="text-align: center;">(signature of applicant/applicant:SÂ· solicitor)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Notice to respondent</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">To: Chief Psychiatrist Cl-ACT Government Solicitor PO Box 260 Civic Square, ACT 2608<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Â·</p><p style="text-align: center;">Before taking any other step in this proceeding, you must file a notice of intention to respond in the Court and serve a sealed copy of it on the appellant.</p><p style="text-align: center;">If you want to present evidence, you must file affidavits in the Court, and serve stamped copies of them on the appellant, not later than 14 days after the day the application is served on you.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">*omit if, or whichever is, inapplicable</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">AF2006-387<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Form 5.3-Supreme Court-application for leave to appeal out</p><p style="text-align: center;">of time</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">page2</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Legal Aid ACT</p><p style="text-align: center;">'"""""-=--===---=-=</p><p style="text-align: center;">CLIENT SERVICES</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">17 January 2019</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Wendell Nesmith XXXXXX</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Mr Nesmith</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mental health, 19G341673X</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Eligibility for Legal Aid is determined by the Commission's Guidelines. We look carefully at your financial eligibility, the merits of your case and whether it complies with requirements of the Legal Aid Act.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Taking into account these guidelines, your application for legal assistance has been refused because it is not reasonable to spend scarce legal aid funds in circumstances where prospects of success are outside our guidelines of more likely than not to succeed.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">You can ask for this decision to be reconsidered. If you want to do so, please send your request in writing to Client Services within 28 days.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Yours sincerely</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Client Services Legal Aid ACT Ph: 6243 3411</p><p style="text-align: center;">Fax: 6243 3435</p><p style="text-align: center;">client.services@legalaidACT.org.au</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">GENERAL CONDITIONS OF LEGAL ASSISTANCE</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Your obligations</p><p style="text-align: center;">1. Your initial contribution towards the cost of the legal work covered by the grant of legal assistance is noted on the reverse side of this document. You must pay this contribution to your lawyer at your next appointment.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">2. We may reassess the amount of your contribution and increase it (even up to 100% of the full cost of providing assistance}. Call our Client Services staff on 6243 3411 if you want to know more about the circumstances in which your contribution might be increased.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">3. If your lawyer receives any money on your behalf, they must keep sufficient aside to pay us any contribution that you owe. Contributions are paycib1e on demand. If you are having difficulty paying your contribution, you may ask us if you can pay'y.insfafments.</p><p style="text-align: center;">4. If you or 4oneen whom you depend for financial support owns any land (e.g. a house er unit) we may make it a condi.ion of the grant of legal assistance that we take a charge over that land to secure payment of your contribution.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">5. You must notify us imrne.diately if there is any change in your financial situation, or if you change address.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">6. If you do net accept your lawyer's advice, your grant of legal assistance may be stopped.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">7. You must get our approval before you change your lawyer. If you do change your lawyer you may have to pay additional costs because of this.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">8. The documents we hold concerning your grant of legal assistance will be destroyed seven years after the grant is completed, unless you ask us to make other arrangements.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Your rights of review</p><p style="text-align: center;">9. For most decisions we make you may request a reconsideration if you are not satisfied with the decision. The request must be made in writing within 28 days of receiving notice of the decision. If you are not satisfied with the result of the reconsideration, you may request an independent review of the decision. The request for review must be made in writing within 28 days of notification of the result of the reconsideration.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">10. Legal Aid ACT will be impartial and open in our dealings with you. We will provide accurate information within a reasonable timeframe.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Your lawyer's obligations</p><p style="text-align: center;">11 Your lawyer has been authorised by us to do the work described in the grant of assistance up to the commitment limit set in the grant. If more work needs to be done your lawyer must first ask us to extend the grant of assistance.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">12. Your lawyer must not ask you to pay anything towards the cost of work covered by the grant of assistance, other than your contribution.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">13. Your lawyer must give us reports on the progress of your case, and details of any offers to settle the case. As your case progresses, your lawyer must provide a report on the outcomes reached and an account setting out the work they have done and the cost of that work.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">14. Your lawyer must make their file available to us if we ask to see it.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">15. Your lawyer must comply with professional standards as a legal practitioner and also comply with practice standards developed by Legal Aid ACT for legal assistance work. The practice standards can be viewed on the Legal Aid ACT website; www.legalaidact.org.au</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">If you want a further explanation of any of these terms and conditions please contact Client Services on 6243 3411 during business hours.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ACT CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Our Ref:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH</p><p style="text-align: center;">XXXXXX</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Notice of Hearing</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH-MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The ACT Civil and Administrative Tribunal is holding a hearing to review a Psychiatric Treatment Order.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Tribunal has listed this matter as outlined below:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">HEARING</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br