idence etc. WIii not trial any medlcotion as he belleves he Is well and that any medication for his mental health is medical doctors trying'to censor him or forsome other ill intent or for our benefit/gain</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Relevant Past History</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith has only had two prior contact periods with our Service.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The first was In April 2012, referred by GP, resulting In a short involuntary PSU (acute adult psychiatric ward) admission, Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The referral from GP stated "I-le presented to me with some mag/ca/ thinking;no auditory hallucinations; he has no friends and claimed to be living on the mountain. There Is a family history of schizoid personality disorder. I believe he has sch/zotypa/ personality disorder."</p><p style="text-align: center;">He was seen by CATT clinicians, with Mr Nesmith agreeable to coming to hospital for an as.sessment but he had</p><p style="text-align: center;">told CATT "that our system wfll not help; that this is the #2 in a psychiatric ward; your doctors will diagnose me as either schizophrenia or sch/zotypa/; they will force medication on me and push their own Ideal of what a bWiRAA:tt0r+s1.J/nru;..cbsu/r:IJ:i@;+-JM11Lbe-!!rnpr:eGB&wr.11JÂ·t-hM0dribG0t1dftiGGS:t.hat--hwu_g/:Jt..abe;,11t..,JJ\lhCJ 1nP1=wilkb</p><p style="text-align: center;">.....-Â  ...-.;gnored-and-st/gmas-wi//-be-pushed-on-meJ-dootors-wll/-mlsjudge-what-they-see-/nJront-ofthem-and-categorise-- â€¢Â·-Â· Â·Â·</p><p style="text-align: center;">me; your systems do not help BUT/ no longer care about anything so thefoliles of your society wlil have to deal with its creation: ME OR I end my life. Your choice. I no longer care."</p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith was assessed by a psychiatrist Dr J cubis who thought he had a likely psychotic illness or schlzotypal personality disorder. Mr Nesmith was admitted to PSU (acute adult mental health unit) on 28th April - 5th May 2012, Mr Nesmith did not talk or cooperate much with the admission and as he was not floridly psychotic, the team could not uphold a PTO, so he was discharged and lost contact with services,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The second contact was brief in 2013 by the psychiatry c/L Canberra HospItal team after a bizarre Incident where he had inserted speaker wire Into his penis requiring surgical Intervention. Surgical team referred to psychiatry C/L as his speech was hard to follow, he had odd behaviours/beliefs, and seemed quite paranoid. He was lnltlally placed on an ED7 as presented psychotic with thought disorder and grandiose, But this was taken off a few days later as he presented more settled with no evidence of psychosis, though his odd and eccentric personality, paranoid themes and alternate lifestyle (camping In busliland near Mt Ainslie to avoid</p><p style="text-align: center;">people) was noted at the time. He was hence discharged, and not seen again hY our services until this year.</p><p style="text-align: center;">When asked about this hospital Incident r cently Mr Nesmith talked about being "embarrassed" It had happened and that It was "sexual. experimentation" that went horribly wrong, as he wanting to try and "Increase sexual stimulation".</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In regards to other psychiatric presentations, Mr Nesmith has spoken about being "locked up" In hospitals in various places In NSW, at least on 2 occasions, With him believing he was being "censored" for his beliefs and part of a greater conspiracy and cover-up. He was reluctant to give details of his time In hospital or precise locations. He could 11st by name several antlpsychotlcs used (olanzapine, risperidone, quetlaplne) and the awful side effects experienced, adding to his negative experience. It does not seem he has ever taken an\lpsychotlcs long-term, only In restrictive environments.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar) Printed By: Dr Caroline Fly_nn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 8 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">There Is no known history of his earlier years In the US before he moved to Australia. He states he Is estranged from his us parents and siblings because they 11don't believe In my cause". He Is adamant he does not want contact with them, We have not found any longer-term friend or contact for any collateral history alas.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DECISION-MAl(ING CAPACITY</p><p style="text-align: center;">5. Â· Does the person, or can the person [with assistance If needed):</p><p style="text-align: center;">[a) Understand When a decision about treatment, care or support needs to be made?</p><p style="text-align: center;">D Yes<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>IBl No</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(b) Understand the facts that relate to the decision?</p><p style="text-align: center;">(c) Understand 