ust 2018 9:01 AM</p><p style="text-align: center;">To: ACAT, Mental Health <ACATMentalHealth@act.gov.au></p><p style="text-align: center;">Cc: Thomas, Kell (Health) <Kell.Thomas@act.gov.au>; City Mental Health Team</p><p style="text-align: center;"><CityMentalHealthTeam@act.gov.au></p><p style="text-align: center;">Subject: RE: MH 108/2012 WN [SEC=UNCLASSIFIED, DLM=Sensitive]</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Good morning,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Kell Thomas has uploaded hospital notes from both Ballarat and Cairns hospitals, please advise if you want these emailed to you.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell has been engaging with City mental health, accepting treatment and psychiatric review to avoid "further</p><p style="text-align: center;">torture" ie going back to hospital. I'm sure the CM will attend the hearing and provide the Tribunal with further information as requested.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Impression after psychiatric review on 31/7/18:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">"Remains very fixed around his beliefs but seems less driven then prior to hospitalization. Very grandiose.</p><p style="text-align: center;">No insight that he has a psychotic illness.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Is agreeing to have treatment because of fears of "further torture" eg going back to hospital. Engagement will continue to be fraught with this tension but currently was able to establish good rapport today."</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Ongoing plan:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Continue olanzapine depot. Consider dose increase.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Need to arrange new GP@ Interchange. Needs to start process of DSP Housing support - need to explore all emergency/temporary housing options</p><p style="text-align: center;">Centrelink Certificate - dated until mid-october; diagnosis - schizophrenia - see scanned copy Case manager to look into psychological and other support.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I hope this is of some assistance to the Tribunal. Regards,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Sharon Steele</p><p style="text-align: center;">Tribunal Liaison Officer</p><p style="text-align: center;">Mental Health, Justice Health and Alcohol & Drug Services</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Level 1</p><p style="text-align: center;">Building 25</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;">Phone: 02 61745410</p><p style="text-align: center;">Fax:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>02 62444558</p><p style="text-align: center;">E-mail:Â  Sharon.Steele@act.gov.au</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">CMJSrnRt, HOSP11'.41</p><p style="text-align: center;">AND HEALTH SERVICES</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">From: ACAT, Mental Health</p><p style="text-align: center;">Sent: Wednesday, 1 August 2018 4:35 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">To: Tribunal Liaison <TribunalLiaison@act.gov.au></p><p style="text-align: center;">Subject: MH 108/2012 WN [SEC=UNCLASSIFIED, DLM=Sensitive]</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Good afternoon,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">At the hearing on 12 July 2018, the Tribunal asked that they receive further information in relation to Wendell Nesmith.</p>