/p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No. Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">28/04/2012 01:12 AM: - [File Note- assessment at MHAU] (Completed 28/04/2012 02:29 AM) assessment at MHAU</p><p style="text-align: center;">Please see full assessment by Jon Wells for more detailed information.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PC:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Brought in by CATT after Ainslie Village worker notified CATT, was worried about increasing mention</p><p style="text-align: center;">?bout suicide.</p><p style="text-align: center;">'-</p><p style="text-align: center;">HPC and past psych Hx:</p><p style="text-align: center;">full extent unclear, but dropped out of uni, estranged from family</p><p style="text-align: center;">had psych admission (?in VIC) for 6 weeks (he thinks it hasn't helped at all, meds were not helpful) has been living in Canberra for about a year, some of that time on Mt Ainslie in a tent writing philosophical texts</p><p style="text-align: center;">grandiose delusional context in this, having created his own religion, talking to God, contemplating suicide</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Medical:</p><p style="text-align: center;">denies any medical illness, signs that he is "strong" says no allergies</p><p style="text-align: center;">refused all medical exams, ECG, blood tests</p><p style="text-align: center;">drugs have not been mentioned in any former reports, mental state seems to be relatively stable over time</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MSE:</p><p style="text-align: center;">v â€¢mg man of stated age</p><p style="text-align: center;">L.1ssed in outdoor clothes, slightly disheveled with moderately strong body odour</p><p style="text-align: center;">only communicating by signing, writing on notepad and playing prerecorded messages on his phone (which seem to have been prewritten before recording, spoken with slight American accent)</p><p style="text-align: center;">some eye contact</p><p style="text-align: center;">at first cooperative, sat down in armchair opposite me and played his phone message. Then when I asked him how long the message is going to be (after some minutes), he became angry, wrote "f... you" on his notepad, went back to bed, pulled blanket over his head, continued to communicate by signing though. This was only a brief episode and soon he was as before, remained calm and did not threaten us, not agitated.</p><p style="text-align: center;">no cognitve disturbance noted, however not formally tested (incl. orientation)</p><p style="text-align: center;">no FTD noted, however difficult to assess while mute (internet page quite well structured, phone message as well)</p><p style="text-align: center;">thought content: philosophical about meaning of life, not being loved enough, how God could create</p><p style="text-align: center;">something special like him and then not use him ("I am like an unused solar panel", "not connected to the grid"), contemplating suicide as option, no clear plan to our knowledge</p><p style="text-align: center;">perceptions: unclear mood: unclear</p><p style="text-align: center;">affect: at first quite restricted and guarded, then slightly dysphoric</p><p style="text-align: center;">risk: mention of suicide as option in his messages, no obvious risk to others</p><p style="text-align: center;">insight and judgement: some insight in mental disorder (some weeks ago thought he might have schizotypal PD, however does not think he has schizophrenia), judgement seems impaired</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Steele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:29:36</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">IIIIIIIIllIIIllIIIll IllIIIllIIIII</p><p style="text-align: center;">*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Wendell Ct DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> 2 Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 To<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown 9999</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Impression:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Young man with Hx of psychiatric disorder, currently with psychotic syndrome, probably diagnosis of schizophrenia (DD: very severe personality disorder).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Plan (D/W Dr Murphy, psychiatrist on call):</p><p style="text-align: center;">- admit on ED3</p><p style="text-align: center;">- chart Olanzapine at present if he wishes to take same or if becomes agitated</p><p style="text-align: center;">- attempt medical exam again tomorrow (and bloods and ECG)</p><p style="text-align: center;">- RN by psychiatrist on call tomorrow DR FLORIAN WERTENAUER</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">28/04/2012 06:31 AM: - [File Note - Night report.] (Completed 28/04/2012 06:41 AM) On ED3 awaiting a HOU bed.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendall has been noted to have sleep well on all observational rounds.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He remained on MHAU overnight as he was deemed to need a HOU bed rather than an LOU and AMHU reported that only ( male) LOU beds were available. This was not true as 2 HOU beds were apparently empty.</p><p style="text-align: center;">No bed was available to him due to the bed cap having been reached.</p><p style="text-align: center;">At no time during his stay has he spoken to me. He has communicated by writing on paper.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">HOWARD LANFRANCHI</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">28/04/201210:52AM: - [File Note-assessment] (Completed 28/04/201211:27 AM) S/ B Dr Cubis:</p><p style="text-align: center;">27 year old man recently referred to MH because of concerns about being homeless. Some concerns about suicidal risk. Past history of contact with services, but not here. Apparently estranged from family and many schizoid traits at least. Apparently came from Victoria and living as a hermit in bushland around Canberra possibly for a year. Not unequivocally psychotic but very odd and messaniac.Came in voluntary with the crisis team in martyred sort of way. Convinced will not be managed by the mental health system. Communicating about suicide on his website. Refuses to speak mood and affect variable.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Today isolated and moving around ward purposefully. Refused to talk, but irritably scribbled note that I was ignorant and had to go to his website. Did this, but generally reading restricted by security alert from ACT Health. Philosophical themes but several posts about suicide treatise by Hume and content on death, "last stand". Mostly critic of bio-psychosocial medical model of care. Presented initially a black folded swan and declaration on paper. Generally hostile, refusing to speak irritated and frustrated by situation. Not really very distressed, more petulant. Affect flat slightly grandiose intense and justified</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by:Â  Sharon Sleele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/20Â·12 Â·I0:29:38</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">'111111111111 IllIIIll111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Numb