br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress -SARAH FINLAYSON</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">:;::::::::::::;:::::;:::::;;:::::;;;;:;:::::::;:::;::_</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PrintP.rJ on :<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:24</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR NumberÂ  20163678</p><p style="text-align: center;">I<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Nesmith<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Page No.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>26</p><p style="text-align: center;">First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Wendell Ct</p><p style="text-align: center;">DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 04:56 AM: - [File Note - nocte nursing note] (DRAFT - last modified 03/05/2012 05:01 AM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">F<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>21 Sleep Pattern</p><p style="text-align: center;">D<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Wendell was awake at the commencement of the shift but retired to his bedroom shortly afterward without engaging with staff. He was observed to be asleep on the floor of his bedroom until 0045 when he began reading a book whilst remaining on the floor. He refused the offerof PRN to help him sleep, notably he did this with the use of gestures not words. When staff asked Wendell what he was reading he simply showed them the book and continued reading. At 0145 Wendell stopped reading and was observed to be sleeping on his bedroom floor. He was observed to be sleeping there on all subsequent rounds until TOR</p><p style="text-align: center;">A</p><p style="text-align: center;">R</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">New Issues/Exceptions</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PETER DEXTER</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 12:13 PM: - [File Note - Psychiatry review] (Completed 03/05/2012 12:17 PM) Psychiatry review Dr. Moore, Dr. Dasgupta & Dr. Kim</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell has started speaking with a nurse but he still refuses to talk to the treating team. He has agreed for the Psychologist to see him but he refuses to cooperate with the team.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Plan</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">1. Transfer him to LDU</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">2. No leave at present</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">3. PTO hearing Monday afternoon</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">4. Psychologist to see him</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - DR RANA DASGUPTA</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><span style="white-space: normal;"><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Prinf13.,-I nn â€¢</span></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Ill</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Wendell Ct</p><p style="text-align: center;">DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 12:51 PM: - [File Note -AM Nursing Notes -t/fto LOU] (DRAFT- last modified 03/05/2012 04:43 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">F</p><p style="text-align: center;">D<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Continuing to refuse to speak to select staff members. When Wendell does engage, he is pleasant, warm and polite. Increased quantity of speech, slightly rapid, occasionally difficult to break conversation. Continues to talk about being a philosopher and that loneliness is one of his biggest problems. Also says he believes in love, and that he just wants to be listened to and understood. Denies AH;VH; nil evidence of responding to internal stimuli; very well spoken. Does express some delusions of grandeur, regarding his website and his importance. Reports wanting to expose flaws in the mental health system; states "the world is watching", and ifhe dies either in hospital or when discharged it will be clear that it is on our(mental health ACT) hands.States has constant suicidal ideation, that he is happy to die as he is alone and his life's work is done, but did not appear to authorto have an active plan. Reports mood as "great"; affect reactive. Using good eye contact.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Settled behaviour; participating in art group.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Refusing to speak with treating team still. Very unhappy that the doctors would not communicate with him unless he is able to write. Appears quite fearful of the mental health system, has likely had negative experiences in Victoria.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Believes if he speaks he won't be listened to anyway and his words will be taken out of context. Afraid of being given injections against his will, does not want any medications or</p><p style="text-align: center;">.think these are necessary. ?Personality disorder traits becoming observable.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Transferred to LOU room P11 at lunch time.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">New</p><p style="text-align: center;">lss ues/Exceptions</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">: A.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>. Nilroutine niedicat1ons charted.Given hospital paj.,mos,</p><p style="text-align: center;">. cls!on tow ls nd soap; enco!Jfi!ged.to.haveashm,yer; Clothes washed: Has been tai<ing y()ghurt and juices.â€¢.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â· .observati'oi:is taken as charted, .<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>_Â· Â·Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>. Â· _Â·Â· ..<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Â·. Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Enco4raged to speak with_ welfare officer Judy lvloore re, :</p><p style="text-align: center;">Centrelink payments, has declined to do so.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>. .</p><p style="text-align: center;">R<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Settled in LDU; orientated to new environment.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress -SARAH FINLAYSON</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Stoolo<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:27</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">IIIIIIIIllIIIllIIIllII IllIIIllIIIII</p><p style="text-align: center;">*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR NumberÂ  20163678</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Surname</p><p style="text-align: center;">First Name</p><p style="text-align: center;">Nesmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Ct</p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.</p><p style="text-align: center;">28</p><p style="text-align: center;">DOB</p><p style="text-align: center;">27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender</p><p style="text-align: center;">Male</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address</p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 01:07 PM : - [File Note - Psychology session] (DR AFT - last modified 03/05/2012 02:59 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I met with Wendell in the interview room in the HDU. Wendell was dressed in hospital pajamas and appeared to be showered and well groomed. Wendell initially would not speak to me and would only answer questions by writing down the answer (see below for verbatim responses to questions). He maintained appropriate eye contact through out our session although his stare was often intense and his affect was responsive and appropriately emotive. Once Wendell began to speak, his speech was pressured and fluent and no thought disorder was present. Wendell did have some grandiose ideas, believing that his philosophy website would change the world and make him famous once he died. No abnormal perceptions were noted, he was able to follow the conversation easily, and was not distracted. He was oriented to time and place but showed minimal insight, stating that his reason for admission was because he "handed him self in". I did not observe any obvious psychotic phenomena.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Initially I asked Wendell why he would not speak to anyone. His written response was "Your people have screwed me bad in the past. I don't trust psychiatrist. I like psychologist."</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I again tried to encourage Wendell to talk, explaining therapy would be difficult otherwise. Wendell responded "Last time I talked to you guys would not listen. Cut me off and took my words out of context and used them to medicate me with inappropriate medications. Claimed me as delusional. My life was delusional to you people."</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I then responded that by assuring him that I would not cut him off and that I would listen to him. He stated "Promise me NO forced medications and hear out metaphors. Everything in our existence is NOT literal. Know Plato's cave?The matrix. Your biomedical conception of reality is only one perspective of reality".</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I again reassured him that I would listen to his metaphors but that I had absolutely no control over medications. He responded "I will talk if you drop your preconceptions about what a</p><p style="text-align: center;">. person "should" be. I am not that person".</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I assured him that I had no preconceptions of him and he spoke fluently following this.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendall spoke in depth about his philosophical beliefs and about how he had spent his whole life trying to find like minded people. He further discussed that his life was all about love. He told me that he was currently homeless and living in the wilderness. He spoke about his loving and close relationship with animals. He also reported that he has lived in 10 different places over the past 12 months ranging from places in the USA to country town in Australia. This</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Stoolo<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printod on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:29</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">report was incongruent with his report of having no money or Centrelink payments.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">When I spoke to Wendell about suicide, he reported that he had chronic suicidal ideation. He had no immediate plan but did report that in the past he had thought about cutting his wrists along his tattoo. He spoke about some future plans (continuing his philosophy work) but also reported feelings of loneliness.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell was then moved to LDU.</p><p style="text-align: center;">.r</p><p style="text-align: center;">('. ,;at with Wendell during the community lunch and he continued to speak with myself and the</p><p style="text-align: center;">others at the table, he reported that he liked LOU and reported some hope that he may be able to get some help here.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Sally Patrick Psychologist</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Supervised by Amaly Khalaf</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - SALLY PATRICK</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 01:42 PM: - [File Note - TLO - Notice of Tribunal hearing] (DRAFT- last modified</p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 01:51 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Application for a Psychiatric Treatment Order to be heard before ACAT on Monday 7 May 2012 at</p><p style="text-align: center;">2r.30pm.</p><p style="text-align: center;">\/\fendell was initially happy to talk to me about the PTO application and notice of hearing. He asked what the point of it all was and I told him that treating team believe that he may need ongoing mental health treatment. I told him that if a PTO was made, it would compel him to take medication. At this point he got up and started to walk away. I asked him to come back and find out what the proposed treatment is, which he did. Proposed treatment is possibly depot injection and Wendell then walked away, refused to take the papers or talk anymore.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">He did not comment when I offered Legal Aid or PMCT. I will ensure that Legal Aid see him prior to the hearing with a view to representation.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - SHARON STEELE</p><p style="text-align: center;">=============</p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 02:10 PM : - [File Note -Art Psychotherapy] (DRAFT - last modified 03/05/2012 02:16 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Art Pyschotherapy:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Creative expression is used therapeutically in a group setting to work towards patients wellbeing. Art Therapy sessions vary from session to session or may continue on from one to the other with a running</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Steele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:32</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">111111111111 11111111111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Wendell Ct DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>30</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">theme or particular work that is happening. Issues related to the patient are discussed in relation to the image and also if the patient just wants to talk (unrelated to art making).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 3rd:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Description: In HOU this morning.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Result:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell: Wendell wrote some notes to him and I accepted them as I did not know to do otherwise and I believe in a therapeutic role I was unable to reject them. Via notes there was a reasonably good exchange. He wrote that he was estranged and alone and had no friends or family. As he gave another patient a hug to calm them down he spoke about how their are rules here not to give hugs. He was completing Julia's painting of a heart and he painted a broken heart saying that this broken hear represented his life. He does have some power with the note writing but it is better than not communicating at all for an attempt at a therapeutic intervention.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - HOLLY EDWORTHY</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 03:35 PM : - [File Note - Psychology group attendance -Active Contact] (DRAFT - last modified 0?05/2012 03:40 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Attended psychology group focused on sleep hygiene.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell reoprted that he did not currently have any sleep problems but was interested in learning to "help humanity". He was engaged during the session and talkative though out. He often added information about alternative interventions to discussions. He also spoke a bout his concern regarding medication, we directed the conversation away from this due to other consumers in the group.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - SALLY PATRICK</p><p style="text-align: center;">=====</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Steele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:36</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â· I llllll lllll lllll111111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">'*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Wendell Ct DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.Â  31</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 03:48 PM : - [File Note - F/u with presenting social issues - Active Contact] (DRAFT - last modified 03/05/2012 04:04 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">F20</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">D: F/u with Wendell at his request re: Centrelink issue</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">A: Wendell ceased his Austudy payment at his request on the 9/4/2012.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(Â  ,ndell has completed a DSP claim form and TOR completed by GP.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendall raised concerns about not been granted a DSP due to requiring further input from a psychologist to assist with the TOR from the GP, Wendall feels that this is unfair and unjust and is refusing a NSA payment.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendall informed that he is eligible for a NSA payment and forms placed in his paper file to complete when settled in mood.</p><p style="text-align: center;">R: Med cert to be completed by the treating team if Wendall is willing to complete NSA application form.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - JUDITH MOORE</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 04:12 PM : - [File Note - Discussed at AFP Comms] (DRAFT - last modified 03/05/2012 04:28 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Discussed at AFP Comms</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>,ndell's father Richard has contacted Glen Waverley Police in Victoria to report his son as a missing person. Richard received emails from Wendell on 26 April stating that he was going to kill himselfÂ­ father has not heard from Wendell since this time.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Richard's contacts are: LL: /03) 851 094 34 /mobile)- 0416 658 156</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Reviewed MHAGIC notes in which Full Ax requests that family are not contacted-AFP will feedback to Victorian Police that Wendell is alive however whereabouts will not be disclosed.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PC to AMHU- no answer PLAN</p><p style="text-align: center;">Msg AMHU re Father's contact</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ALICIA DANKIW</p><p style="text-align: center;"><span style="white-space: normal;"><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>-=</span></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 04:16 PM: - [Message] (Completed 03/05/2012 04:17 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed bv : Sharon Steele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:39</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">111111111111 Ill II Ill111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Wendell Ct</p><p style="text-align: center;">DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>32</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress -ALICIA DANKIW</p><p style="text-align: center;">=============</p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 05:09 PM: - [File Note-Art Psychotherapy] (DRAFT- last modified 03/05/2012 05:13 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Art Pyschotherapy:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Creative expression is used therapeutically in a group setting to work towards patients wellbeing. Art Therapy sessions vary from session to session or may continue on from one to the other with a running theme or particular work that is happening. Issues related to the patient are discussed in relation to the image and also if the patient just wants to talk (unrelated to art making).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 3rd:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Description: In LDU main area.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Result:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell: Wendell tells me he is really angry with the system and that all he was looking for was someone to listen to him with his writing. He has had bad experiences in Vic Mental Health and believes he was falsely labeled. He talks about being an esthetic similar to Buddha living in the bush. He feels his human rights are being toyed with and that he is definitely not mentally unwell. He is a happy person but is just lonely he states living estranged from his family. He stated he would happily die by fasting. I did sense the grandiose re the mastery of his mind and two black belts etc. His image was telling he drew a dog with a very large head... a smiley puppy dog. The body of this dog was very tiny but he stated it could hold this head as it was very strong. He drew one large eye on the dog that was bloodshot but said it was just messiness re the the use of the pastels. I wondered if this dog was him smack bang in the middle of the page all by itself.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - HOLLY EDWORTHY</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">03/05/2012 09:04 PM: - [File Note - Nursing report] (DRAFT - last modified 03/05/2012 09:06 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">F<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Fl Assessment</p><p style="text-align: center;">D<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Wendell has been talking with co-consumers and only speaks with selected staff members. He has voiced nil overt psychotic phenomenon evident.</p><p style="text-align: center;">A<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Ongoing observations.</p><p style="text-align: center;">R<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Ongoing.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">F</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed bv : Sharon Steele</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">New</p><p style="text-align: center;">Issues ft:xceptions</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-al