9999<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>UNK<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">F<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Sleep</p><p style="text-align: center;">D<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>SettledÂ  and sleeping atstartofÂ  shift.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">New Issues/Exceptions</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">A<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Observations maintained.</p><p style="text-align: center;">R<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Observed settled<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>and appeared to be asleep throughout<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>the night.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - EUPHRASIA MARUFU</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">;::::;;::;;:::;:::::::::::::::======</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">04/05/2012 12:21 PM: - [File Note - Ward Round w Dr Javed] (DRAFT - last modified 04/05/2012 12:31 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">10:25 AM in Interview Room w Dr S Javed, Dr J Kim</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell nodded and agreed to being interviewed when asked by Dr Javed. He entered the room and sat down. When asked questions, Wendell stared back in silence, then gestured with his hands to write (as if asking for writing materials).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">We asked him to speak to us, given that he has been reportedly speaking to other staff and patients. He shook his head and made gestures of an injection to his backside (?gesturing he disapproved of Dr's treating him with medications).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">We concluded the interview session as he was unwilling to speak.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell is a thin tall bearded male casually dressed in a black jacket and pants. He calmly entered the interview room and sat in a chair. His speech was difficult to assess as he refused to speak. His mood was unstated and his affect was difficult to gauge. He showed no evidence of formal thought disorder or perceptual disturbances, but could not be properly assessed during the interview. Suicidality was not formally assessed. Insight and judgment were difficult to gauge.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Steele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:46</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â· 111111111111 11111111111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">'*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 ToÂ  07/05/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PLAN:</p><p style="text-align: center;">1. Remain admitted</p><p style="text-align: center;">2. PTO hearing on Monday (07/05/12).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DR JOSEPH KIM</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Wendell Ct DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>UNK</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>35</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">04/05/2012 12:32 PM : - [File Note - Group painting/creative arts therapy -Active Contact] (Completed</p><p style="text-align: center;">04/05/2012 12:40 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;">;1'-</p><p style="text-align: center;">;t</p><p style="text-align: center;">Invited Wendell to group painting, he refused on the grounds that we forced him to take drugs. In the</p><p style="text-align: center;">middle of the group process Wendell appeared with a blue origami flower and tried to incorporated within the drawing that was developing.Caught up with Wendell after the group. I thanked him his contribution and met a totally different person.. He smiled and warmly engaged in the conversation that ensued.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRAFT In Progress - RENALD NAVILLY</p><p style="text-align: center;">=========</p><p style="text-align: center;">04/05/2012 02:32 PM : - [File Note - PC to Father - Collateral History] (DRAFT - last modified</p><p style="text-align: center;">04/05/2012 03:47 PM)</p><p style="text-align: center;">14:10 Phone Call made to Mr Richard Nesmith in VIC</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Spoke to Patient's father and explained that patient is not communicating with treating team, and requested more information. Also stated that I would not be giving him much information regarding</p><p style="text-align: center;">,driagnosis/treatment/plan as patient has not given consent.</p><p style="text-align: center;">'IN SUMMARY:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell moved to Australia around 15 years ago with his family to Perth. Shortly thereafter, in 1997, his</p><p style="text-align: center;">parents divorced with Wendell's mother taking custody of Wendell. Wendell moved out and lived on his own since 17 years of age. He met a woman and married, but later divorced. He has held a few techÂ­ related jobs, but has lost his jobs due to difficulty with co-workers. Wendell has been involved with alcohol and drug issues, which was unbeknownst to Richard.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell relocated several times over the years. After his Wendell and his wife divorced, Wendell moved to the U.S. and lived there for 1 year. He then returned to Melbourne in May/June of 2011. Wendell was admitted to a psychiatry unit sometime in Ballarat(VIC), but absconded and never returned to the psychiatry unit during his unaccompanied leave. Wendell then moved back to Perth where he had a few friends and connections, but later exhausted those relationships. He then moved to ?Nimbin town, a "hippy drug culture" town north of Sydney in November 2011. Wendell resided in hospices, but later bought a tent and began living in the woods until Feb/Mar 2012. He subsequently moved to Canberra.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell believes he is an enlightened philosopher and has sad views of the world. He hosts a philosophy-based website at Nesmith.net.au in which he posts a series about his views. In one of his final series, titled something to degree of 'Examining my Death' he posts a video of himself with a knife, cutting across his chest, yelling things at the camera, then covering the camera's view. Richard believes this is for 'show,' as Wendell has not explicitly stated suicidal intent and is careful with his choice of words. Richard stated that he had scars on his forearms from slitting his wrists.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Steele<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/2012 10:30:50</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">111111111111 IIIIIIll111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Patient Progress</p><p style="text-align: center;">From<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>28/04/2012 To 07/05/2012 PMHx</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Wendell Ct DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;">Address<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Unknown</p><p style="text-align: center;">9999<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>UNK</p><p style="text-align: center;">Home Phone Unknown Work Phone</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page No.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>36</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Male</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">NA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell has always been healthy. No reported past medical conditions or illnesses. Richard described</p><p style="text-align: center;">him as a hypochondriac at times and becoming demanding.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell's ex-wife reported in an email to Richard that Wendell had joint problems.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PSYHx</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell was diagnosed as having schizophrenia while in Ballarat. He disagreed with the diagnosis, but</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">RX</p><p style="text-align: center;">No known regular medications. It was unclear if he was on pain medications at some point because of</p><p style="text-align: center;">joint problems.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DRUGS AND ETOH</p><p style="text-align: center;">Richard states he caught Wendell smoking something when he was around 17 years of age. Wendell denied it as being marijuana, and called it 'skoggies,' something he made himself. Richard states he did not smell marijuana.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell was reprimanded for bringing Ritalin (methylphenidate) to school in 1998-1999. Richard reports</p><p style="text-align: center;">it was unclear whether he was dealing drugs.</p><p style="text-align: center;">In 2003/2004, Richard reported that Wendell's ex-wife had reported Wendell was drinking heavily, usually spirits and beers.</p><p style="text-align: center;">According to an email Richard received from Wendell's ex-wife, Wendell has also been abusing many</p><p style="text-align: center;">substances, including: Lorazepam; Stilnox; Cannabinoids; Kaba Kaba; and a self-made herbal mixture called Passion Flower, which was his drug of choice.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">EDUCATION/OCCUPATION</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell attended a Christian school for 1 year while in Perth, and later attended a nearby technical school. He completed his high school (Year 12) education. When he reached 17 years of age and was able to receive a Dole Pension, he left home.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell excelled at school. He could have been placed into a year higher than what he was back in the U.S., but chose to remain in the year he was placed.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell has been reportedly taking philosophy and religion courses through Murdoch University's distance education. He reportedly clashed with his professors. Richard reports Wendell feels "enlightened" and feels sorry for the world.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell has held 3-4 tech related jobs, and was almost promoted to a manager's position in one of his jobs. He has had difficulties keeping his job however, because he had difficulties getting along with coÂ­ workers.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Though Wendell disagrees about being diagnosed with schizophrenia, he has been seeing doctors to</p><p style="text-align: center;">corroborate and provide documentation to be on a pension. His father believes that he is malingering and trying to avoid working by being labeled with a disability. He has reportedly burned identity documents with the intent of qualifying as a disabled person.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">SOCIAL ISSUES</p><p style="text-align: center;">Richard described Wendell as being "Mr. Smooth" among his peers and being a leader which his peers looked up to. However he eventually strained and destroyed all of his relationships, as his friends were "either with him or against him." A lot of his relationships ended with anger and bitterness.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Richard reported that Wendell's hobbies included Karate, which he was passionate about and was enrolled in classes. He was later doing his Karate through an online organisation, which he may have been awarded a black-bell. Wendell enjoys listening to music and playing the guitar, which his father</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed by : Sharon Stoolo<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Printed on:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>07/05/201210:30:54</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â· 111111111111 IIIII Ill111111111111111</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·*40260*</p><p style="text-align: center;">The Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">UR Number 20163678 Surname<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Nesmith First Name<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span> Wendell Ct DOB<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;