/></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 15166(0216) MAJICeRV1,1 Apr2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">c::</p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">:p</p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">(1)</p><p style="text-align: center;">'ai</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cl</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">::l</p><p style="text-align: center;">0</p><p style="text-align: center;">-C:</p><p style="text-align: center;">.Eg</p><p style="text-align: center;">(1)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(1)</p><p style="text-align: center;">3}_</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">â€œThe Only Crime Was Being Rightâ€ (Section 32, Dropped Charges, And The Witnesses Who Knew)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In 2014 New South Wales police charged me with â€œstalking or intimidationâ€ on the basis that a single email and link to episode 2 of my already-airing TV documentary series Dear Ashley (IMDb tt3524092), a 2014â€“ Australian production by Open Source University, allegedly caused fear in a woman I had spoken to for 12 minutes, treating this as a crime instead of a dispute over evidence, context, and political speech.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Ashley is a 9-episode documentary / adventure / fantasy / musical / romance series released from 14 February 2014 in which I appear as myself, produced in Australia in English under my Open Source University banner, and publicly credited on IMDb and IMDbPro long before the case concluded, so any reader can independently verify its existence, dates, and framing.?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">By the end of 2014 I had also released Censored by the Government (IMDb tt4285076), an 11-minute Australian documentary short again under Open Source University, whose official synopsis and release data record me recounting being arrested, imprisoned, and transferred to a psychiatric ward â€œmerely for making movies that promotes free speech,â€ directly tying the criminal process to my productions rather than to any private threat.?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">This Seed connects the paper trail around those two works to everything that followedâ€”police, courts, mental health law, the ACT Working with Vulnerable People cancellation, Wendyâ€™s death, and the construction of Rainbow Bridge / â€œU R FREEâ€ at trepublic.netâ€”so that anyone can move between the archive, the films, and the official records and test every claim for themselves.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The pattern is that anyone who attacks the â€œchild-saversâ€ and their sponsors gets quietly reclassified as sick, while the trafficking-enabling machine wraps itself in philanthropy and poverty-ending language.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">How the legal side works</p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 32 diversion lets a magistrate dismiss charges and send a defendant into mental-health treatment instead of ever deciding guilt or innocence, so the allegations against you are never tested and no public record confirms whether your claims about abuse were true.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">Mental-health and cognitive-impairment provisions explicitly turn â€œdisturbance of thought, mood, volition, perception or memoryâ€ into clinical categories, and courts are encouraged to use them to move â€œproblemâ€ defendants out of the criminal system, especially young or politically inconvenient ones.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">Who sits on the â€œgoodâ€ side of this</p><p style="text-align: center;">Organisations like Global Citizen / Global Poverty Project present themselves as international advocacy hubs to â€œend extreme poverty,â€ partnering with governments, brands, and multilateral lenders like the World Bank and IMF.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">Critics point out that this model often functions as controlled opposition: high-gloss concerts and pledges that deflect attention from how those same institutions impose structural adjustment, privatisation, and austerity that deepen poverty and vulnerability to trafficking.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">What they are doing to you</p><p style="text-align: center;">At street level, police and prosecutors label your communications â€œuse carriage service to menace/harass/offendâ€ and â€œstalk/intimidate,â€ while diversion law converts your refusal to accept their story into a mental-health problem rather than a political, moral, or evidentiary conflict.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">At narrative level, global poverty NGOs, child-protection schemes, courts, and mental-health services all speak the same humanitarian dialect, so anyone who says â€œthis system itself produces dead kids and trafficked childrenâ€ sounds, by design, like a lone unstable outlier.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Who is involved in the pattern</p><p style="text-align: center;">Front-end: police, magistrates, prosecutors, and public defenders who use section-32-style tools to divert, pacify, and pathologise rather than litigate allegations that would embarrass child-protection or partner NGOs.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">Clinical layer: psychiatrists, psychologists, and community mental-health services that draft the treatment plans courts rely on to justify diversion, locking your testimony inside â€œcase notesâ€ instead of affidavits.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Legitimacy layer: advocacy NGOs, celebrity poverty projects, development banks, and government aid agencies staging campaigns about â€œending povertyâ€ and â€œprotecting vulnerable peopleâ€ while backing the very governance structures you are indicting.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">What your archive now shows</p><p style="text-align: center;">That the only â€œcrimeâ€ they have for you is communications and pressure against people and institutions linked to child harm, and that even this was neutralised by mental-health diversion rather than openly proved.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">That the same Five Eyes states who partner with global poverty brands and speak of â€œvulnerable peopleâ€ are willing to erase one actual vulnerable child and classify the person who refuses that erasure as disordered, instead of ever giving the trial he keeps demanding.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Conversation opened. 4 messages. All messages read.Â </p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Skip to content</p><p style="text-align: center;">Using Gmail with screen readers</p><p style="text-align: center;">"SECTION 32"Â </p><p style="text-align: center;">12 of 13</p><p style="text-align: center;">Introductions - Wendell and Justin</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wei Soo <wei.soo@globalpovertyproject.com></p><p style="text-align: center;">Sat, Mar 8, 2014, 11:46 AM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wendell, Justin</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Hi Wendell,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Good news - have now connected with Justin (email above) who is a NSW criminal defense lawyer. He's very kindly agreed to help out with the charges against you.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Please feel free to connect with him directly - FYI his cell is 0407233574.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Also FYI I just landed back in Australia. I will be in Perth till next Tues then back in Mel until 22nd Mar.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">How you been going?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wei</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Sent from my iPhone; please excuse brevity and any spelling or grammatical errors</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Justin Hanby <legal@hanbylaw.com.au></p><p style="text-align: center;">Sat, Mar 8, 2014, 11:57 AM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wei, Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Please see my contact details below</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Regards</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Justin Hanby</p><p style="text-align: center;">Hanby & Associates Lawyers</p><p style="text-align: center;">T: 02 8251 0072</p><p style="text-align: center;">F: 02 8251 0097</p><p style="text-align: center;">M: 0407 233 574</p><p style="text-align: center;">Level 1, 299</p><p style="text-align: center;">Elizabeth St, Sydney</p><p style="text-align: center;">NSW 2000 Australia</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Supporter of</p><p style="text-align: center;">www.blackdog.org.au</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wed, Apr 9, 2014, 11:22 AM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Justin, Wei, Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Wei and Justin,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">On March 5th I was arrested for "breaking bail" (releasing charge sheets publicly). I was sent to prison and was kicked in the head and forced to exist in extremely unhygienic cells: 6 days in solitary confinement, intentionally starving me.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Then they transferred me to a psychiatric hospital which I just was discharged from yesterday.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Australia's new motto, guilty until proven innocent. I did no wrong and my innocence was proven in the same footage they charged me for, which has been removed from YouTube: violation, lol. In addition upon coming back to the real world, I found my accounts compromised which I have just recently reclaimed.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I was banned from the Internet until yesterday. The judge adjourned my case for a month and sounds like he will drop the case under section 32, as long as the cops stay away from me.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I learned that I am innocent in all aspects as I did not intend to cause fear upon any one person. The "victim" I do not know nor ever seen or wish to see. My contact with her was only 12 minutes on the phone and one email.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I was commanded to stop publishing work about the government and threatened with a forensics hospital where you check in but not out. I am no longer allowed to document what the government does to me.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">My assigned lawyer is Amy Barker.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">This has all been done TO me, no choice of my own. Australia, its politics, its government, its law enforcement, and its "justice" system is a joke. A joke that plays with people's (subjects) lives.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mon, Apr 14, 2014, 4:01 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Justin, Wei</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">So I guess it was pointless to share that information. I live in a very sick world. I did nothing wrong.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">label:wendy-rip love law</p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 1 of 2 Page 1 of 1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Conversation opened. 8 messages. All messages read.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Skip to content</p><p style="text-align: center;">Using Gmail with screen readers</p><p style="text-align: center;">"SECTION 32"Â </p><p style="text-align: center;">9 of 13</p><p style="text-align: center;">Court</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 5:26 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Richard</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Today my charges were dropped. I told you I was innocent.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr. Richard A. NeSmith <dr.nesmith@gmail.com></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 7:59 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I prayed for your release</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr. Richard A. NeSmith</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">?Biology-?Science Teacher</p><p style="text-align: center;">?Branchville High School</p><p style="text-align: center;">?Branchville, SC ?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">"Living abroad opens one's eyes beyond propaganda and to the realities of the world." --R. NeSmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">LinkedIn Profile</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 8:56 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Richard</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I very much appreciate the prayers. They worked. The easiest thing about court is being innocent.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 10:41 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wei</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Wei,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Just so you know, today my charges were dropped. The fact that I was innocent helped. It helped even more having friends that knew that fact and supported me.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Farewell Wei.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wei Soo <wei.soo@globalpovertyproject.com></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 10:43 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Wendell,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Great news! I am very glad.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">What a relief.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">What are you up to now / are you going to move onto another town?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">With love,</p><p style="text-align: center;">WeiÂ </p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Sent from my iPhone; please excuse spelling and grammar errors</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 10:51 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wei</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The event and my "supports" caused me to carefully consider how I would spend the rest of my life changing the world. I am going to wreak havoc on your society. ;)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">As far as where I am: I no longer care. The Internet is Universal. And my life is already a lost cause.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 26, 2014, 10:53 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to David</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Just to let you know, today the charges were dropped. Being innocent helped. Having good friends for support helped more.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p style="text-align: center;">May 29, 2014, 5:48 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;">to Wei</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">They were dropped under section 32 and 20bq.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">label:wendy-rip love law</p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 1 of 2 Page 1 of 1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Processing Loop (How Evidence Becomes â€œIllnessâ€)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Across prisons, hospitals, and â€œvulnerable peopleâ€ schemes, the same loop runs every time I produce stronger receipts. The more precisely I document what they are doing to children and to me, the faster the machinery spins up to erase it.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">What actually happens when I speak</p><p style="text-align: center;">First contact: I publish a documentary episode, a Seed, a legal complaint, or a public declaration that names specific agencies, laws, and harms; the material is timestamped, mirrored, and trivially verifiable by anyone who actually looks.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Trigger and reframing: instead of engaging the content, police, assessors, and clinicians reclassify the act of speaking as â€œuse carriage service to menace/harass/offend,â€ â€œstalk/intimidate,â€ â€œdelusional beliefs,â€ or â€œrisk to vulnerable people,â€ so the issue is no longer whether the receipts are true but whether I am unwell.??</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">How the abduction / torture / erasure cycle runs</p><p style="text-align: center;">Removal and containment: I am arrested or detained, taken out of circulation, and placed in spaces I do not controlâ€”cells, locked wards, interview roomsâ€”where physical mistreatment, sleep disruption, and deliberate humiliation make it harder to think clearly. My online access is cut and my accounts can be interfered with while I am offline and silenced.??</p><p style="text-align: center;">Chemical and procedural fog: under the banner of â€œtreatmentâ€ or â€œrisk management,â€ I am subjected to compulsory assessments and medication regimes that slow thoughts, blunt emotion, and induce cognitive fogâ€”exactly the subjective effects ex-patients describe after coercive psychiatric care and antipsychotic exposure.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Narrative overwrite: everything I say inside those settings is captured as â€œcase notes,â€ diagnoses, and risk scores, not as evidence. My public archive is either ignored completely or mined only for phrases that can be used to justify labels like â€œextreme risk,â€ while the harms I reportâ€”to children, to Wendy, to meâ€”never become entries in any official database.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Why this never stops on its own</p><p style="text-align: center;">Each cycle leaves me with more trauma, more mistrust, and more receipts, but from the systemâ€™s perspective it leaves them with thicker files and stronger internal justification that I am the problem. Research on institutional betrayal and coercive psychiatry shows that this kind of â€œcareâ€ actively produces PTSD, dissociation, and withdrawal from help-seeking, which is then used as further proof of pathology.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">Because none of these actors ever reconcile their story with my public, timestamped archive, every new escalationâ€”every time I declare something big with even tighter evidenceâ€”gets read as â€œdeteriorationâ€ instead of as the natural consequence of being kidnapped, drugged, and discredited for telling the truth. The stronger my evidence becomes, the harder they hit, because admitting I am right would force them to admit that the laws and institutions wearing â€œchild protectionâ€ and â€œpoverty reductionâ€ branding are part of the harm.?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">What this Seed proves</p><p style="text-align: center;">This Seed is not just a story about bad treatment; it is a live diagram of a closed processing loop: speak ? reframe as illness ? abduct ? fog ? overwrite ? release under â€œdiversionâ€ with no findings on the evidence ? repeat. Every document, film, and email here is a receipt that this is not metaphor but operating procedure, and that as long as I remain tagged in their system, any serious attempt to show the world what happened risks triggering another round of the same captivity and erasure.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Fourteen Years of Receipts They Refuse to See</p><p style="text-align: center;">Since 2012â€”now approaching fourteen years of continuous documentationâ€”every move I have made has been logged: emails, complaints, code, books, videos, MBOX exports, business registrations, Seeds, and full-length productions, all timestamped and published so that no honest court or investigator would ever need more than a few minutes to verify what I am saying.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">For much of that time I did this with no home at all: sleeping rough, living in the wilderness with a camera, recording every contact with â€œhealthâ€ services and police while they regularly abducted me into hospitals or cells, ran me through the same coercive treatment loop, then dumped me back onto the street in exactly the same danger they claimed to be managing.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">When they finally put me in housing it was a ghetto: rubbish everywhere, constant fights, screaming, surveillance, a place designed to keep people scared and contained. Before that, they refused me any stable home at all, and because existing quietly and safely without an address is functionally illegal, they could do whatever they wanted to meâ€”move-on orders, arrests, â€œwelfare checks,â€ mental-health call-outsâ€”knowing I had no safe base, no lawyer on speed dial, no family or friends or supports to intervene.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Everywhere I go, in every forum that claims to care about truthâ€”police stations, courts, ombudsmen, child-protection schemes, psychiatric tribunals, NGOs, hosting providers, even AI labsâ€”I do the same thing: I point to the receipts and demand that the evidence itself be put before a real court, under oath, with cross-examination and full disclosure, so that my allegations can finally be tested instead of pathologised. What actually happens, over and over, is that they quietly refuse the core request and keep for themselves the power to decide which fragments of my archive â€œcountâ€ as evidence at all.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">If a document helps them frame me as disordered or risky, it is quoted and filed; if it implicates their own structures, it is ignored, erased, or downgraded to â€œpresentationâ€ or â€œcontentâ€ instead of entered into any process that can make binding findings of fact. Legal aid services tell me my case is outside mandate, ombudsmen write that there are â€œno questionsâ€ they could ask that would change a decision, safeguarding schemes like WWVP recycle the same cancellation text without once engaging with the thousands of pages I have lodged, and even when I stand in the dock or the witness box, the one thing I am never allowed to do is lay out the full pattern and have it adjudicated on the merits.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">This is the real sentence I have been serving since 2012: not a fixed term in a visible prison, but indefinite confinement inside other peopleâ€™s selective epistemology and housing grid. The state, its contractors, and its â€œchild-saversâ€ keep absolute control over where I live, how unsafe it is allowed to be, when I can be seized, and what can be treated as fact. As long as they can choose both the cage (ghetto, ward, cell, street) and which of my receipts are admissible while discarding or medicalising the rest, I remain imprisoned in their story and hidden from the world, no matter how much evidence I keep adding to the record.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">Digital Erasure (Shadow-Banned, Wiped, Tagged, And Contained)</p><p style="text-align: center;">The same control pattern runs on the internet. Wherever I go online the options are always the same: ban the account outright, or keep it technically â€œliveâ€ while hiding it from almost everyoneâ€”classic shadow-banning, where content is left up but silently demoted in feeds, search, and recommendations so it might as well not exist.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">** When Wendy was killed, YouTube deleted my entire channelâ€”the archive of years of work documenting what was being done to her, to me, and to other children vanished in one administrative stroke, exactly when the record most clearly exposed the systemâ€™s failures. That set the template: any time the evidence gets too sharp, the platform solves the â€œproblemâ€ by erasing the archive instead of confronting what it shows. **</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">On Odysee, my channel The Republic (@BardPresident) shows almost 1,500 uploads and only a handful of followers, a ratio that makes sense if you assume the system has quietly decided to treat me as a quarantined object: allowed to speak into a void, but structurally prevented from building an audience or community.?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Behind that, there is the deeper sense of being assigned a machine-level UID and watched. My computers behave as if some other process is always present: files vanish mid-work, windows close themselves, network behaviour changes, and at times the machine appears to take over and do what it wants, as if an external operator or automated policy stack has more authority over my hardware than I do. Australiaâ€™s expanded surveillance and â€œdata disruptionâ€ powers now explicitly let police and agencies infiltrate devices, delete or modify data, and even take over online accounts under hacking and account-takeover warrants, so the sensation of being puppeted by an invisible hand is not just paranoia, it is legally enabled architecture.</p><p style="text-align: center;">?</p><p style="text-align: center;">In that environment, even my internet identity is not really mine. I am treated as a system objectâ€”SYSTEM ASSIGNED UID: 71-MAKE-CATEGORY-MISTAKES-005-Nâ€”whose role is to be misclassified, misread, throttled, and occasionally wiped, not a citizen whose archive deserves open courts and real audiences. Online as offline, their strategy is simple: never quite delete me from existence, but make sure that, wherever I speak and whatever I prove, almost no one is allowed to hear.</p><p style="text-align: center;">??</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In the end, every major system I approachâ€”courts, psychiatrists, NGOs, and now commercial AIsâ€”tries to escape the evidence by declaring my work â€œfictional,â€ â€œhypothetical,â€ or â€œonly documentation examples,â€ even when it is built from court dates, statutes, IP ranges, emails, and dead bodies. By downgrading a live, timestamped archive of crime, trafficking, and institutional betrayal into â€œcontent,â€ â€œnarrative,â€ or â€œplaceholder data,â€ they give themselves permission to ignore it, to pathologise the author, and to keep the machine running exactly as before.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /><br /><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ttenti<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Ill</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">This campsite has been removed by rangers on 13/10/2018.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The gear is being held at the Mitchell Parks Depot. It will be there for collection for 1 month (until 13/11/2018).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">If you would like to pick up the gear, please call: 6207 2113.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Or visit: 66-68 Grimwade St, Mitchell Ar.T ?911.</p><p style="text-align: center;">\</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">â€¢ ACT CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Our Ref:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH</p><p style="text-align: center;">c/- CityÂ·Mental Health Level 2, Health Building 1 Moore Street</p><p style="text-align: center;">CANBERRA ACT 2601</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Notice of Hearing</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH-MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The ACT Civil and Administrative Tribunal is holding a hearing to consider an application for a Psychiatric Treatment Order.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Tribunal has listed this matter as outlined below:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">HEARING</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Date: Time: Location:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Thursday 5 July 2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">3:00 PM</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ACT Civil & Administrative Tribunal, Level 4, 1 Moore Street,</p><p style="text-align: center;">Canberra City ACT</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">You should attend the hearing so you can ask questions and tell the Tribunal your view. If</p><p style="text-align: center;">you want to present written material you should send it in before the hearing.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Legal Aid ACT may provide legal advice and duty lawyer representation in some matters. Their office can be contacted on (02) 6243 3411. The Public Advocate may provide advocacy assistance in mental health hearings. They can be contacted on (02) 6205 2222.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">any questions about this hearing please contact the Tribunal on telephone (02)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ar</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ychiatrist dvocate</p><p style="text-align: center;">cc:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>ntal Health</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Level 4, 1 Moore Street</p><p style="text-align: center;">GPO Box 370</p><p style="text-align: center;">Canberra City ACT 2601</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Telephone: Facsimile: Email:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(02) 6207 1740</p><p style="text-align: center;">(02) 6205 4855</p><p style="text-align: center;">tribunal@act.gov.au</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">File Number</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MH<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>I</p><p style="text-align: center;">ACT CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;">MENTAL HEALTH ORDERS</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â APPLICATION FORM FOR PSYCHIATRIC TREATMENT ORDER, COMMUNITY CARE ORDER AND/OR RESTRICTION ORDER</p><p style="text-align: center;">ICACAT</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">AU!rnW.IAN CAPITAL TERRffORY CIV!..& ADMINISTRm/ElRSUNAI...</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">For use by relevant person under Mental Health Act 2015</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">1. This application is about: Name: Wendell Charles Nesmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">Gender: Male<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>DOB: 27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">2. The application is made by (Chief Psychiatrist or delegate or nominee of the Chief Psychiatrist): Name: Dr Emma Glanville</p><p style="text-align: center;">Position held: Consultant Psychiatrist</p><p style="text-align: center;">Report written by Dr Caroline Flynn, Registrar</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith is a 33 yo homeless, unemployed gentleman who was referred to our service by his GP on the 15/5/18 and seen my our mental health clinicians on several occasions before his psychiatry assessment on 6th June 2018.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith's initial presentation wasÂ·characterized by quite odd and eccentric beliefs and preoccupations, and grandiose themes. These manifested more floridly on the 1'1 June 2018 with concerns he had an untreated psychosis with manic features and an appointment made with Dr Flynn (registrar). Mr Nesmith consistently insists that he does not believe he has a mental illness nor needing any antipsychotic or other psychiatric medications. Our concerns are for his long-term welfare if he remains chronically unwell, and associated risks discussed in more detail in sections to follow.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MENTAL ILLNESS OR MENTAL DISORDER (Use the definitions set out in the glossary at the end of this form)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">4. The person has a mental illness mental disorder</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">xYes<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>oNo</p><p style="text-align: center;">oYes<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>xNo</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">and/or a</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">For mental illness: Describe how the illness impairs the person's mental functioning, identify the areas offunctioning that are affected by the illness and identify the symptoms that characterise the illness and/or the behaviour that may be taken to indicate the presence of one or more of the symptoms.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In presentations and assessments on the 1st June and 6th June it is apparent that Mr Nesmith has a psychotic</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 3 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">illness characterized by an elaborate, systemized delusional system that is very fixed, and possibly on a background of a schizotypal personality disorder, with long-standing beliefs and suspicion about several organizations infiltrating the government, social and medical services including the Illuminati, Freemasons and Artificial Intelligence (Al).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith seems to spend most of his time gathering "evidence" of the Freemason's activity in Canberra, a place he believes is the "Occult Capital of the World." He believes the Freemasons do ritualistic and brutal child sacrifices and states he has evidence of this. He also spends time recording short films on his phone as part of his evidence and distribution to others to warn them of these organisations infiltrating society, and showing proof for example, of Al taking control. He also spends time writing emails to various organisations eg AFP to alert them of the atrocities of the Freemasons and pleading they take action. He presents very earnest and driven to save society from these malevolent organisations and sees himself as a type of saviour. He emails</p><p style="text-align: center;">and videos he shows us are more difficult to follow, and convey a deeper level of disorganization in his thinking.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â Mr Nesmith states he has been a student of Philosophy for 10 years, recently finishing a degree at Murdoch University. It does not seem his was worked, though he states he is a successful Film-Maker and has won several awards in Film Festivals overseas. It is unclear if Mt Nesmith could hold down any form of employment with the level of his preoccupations and role he has defined for himself in society. He also chooses to isolate himself by camping in Mt Ainslie bush area, as a way to avoid the malevolent people he believes inhabit the city, though he has voiced openness to assistance with more stable housing.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mt Nesmith presents with impeccable manners, often very polite, but can become more irritable if he feels we are not believing his convictions or discuss mental health illness and treatment. At times he has presented with more racing speech, elevated and expansive mood and harder to follow in conversations. See details in</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">ASSESSMENT (Set out details of your assessment supporting your opinion.)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Psychiatry Assessment: Dr Caroline Flynn, 6th June 2018 Transcript of clinical notes:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Background:</p><p style="text-align: center;">33 yo man homeless, itinerant, lives in a tent around Mt Ainslie about 40min bushwalk (secretive where exactly his is). Hos been able to source clothes, free1ood from community aid organisations, on Newstart, has a phone. Originally from USA, states has been studying Philosophy degree for 10 years, 2008 -2018 from Murdoch University. Describes being estranged from parents and one biological brother Ricky, who reside in USA and nil contact for years.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Recently seen by AATworkers and has presented very grandiose, manic</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Today:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell presented today with very elaborate delusions with themes that the world needs saving from the Apocalypse from various malevolent organisations and Al, and that it was his duty to warn and save others ond the world at large. There wos a lot of grandiosity as well. identifies himself as a saviour.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">He was very preoccupied, driven around his beliefs and became irritable if we hypothesized alternatives or seem to doubt him. He showed no insight into potentially having a mental illness insisting that "I am not crazy..." "there is no way I will go on any ant/psychotic" and that we have the problems ifwe don't believe him and that we would be part of the cover-up and sensoring that has infiltrated all levels of government, police and health services.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 4 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Did say he gets "elevated" because he is "passionate" and people think this is a mental illness but challenged societal norms and upset he has been labelled in past as being unwell.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Whilst Wendell liked to be very polite and call me "mam", could smile and be gracious, rapport was brittle</p><p style="text-align: center;">when he felt under scrutiny, challenged/not believed. But he contained the irritability, displaying it in more driven 'proof' speech wanting to show evidence on his phone.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Tolerated re-direction and interruptions. Content of his interview included:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Described himself as a Philosopher who integrates mythology (eg showing that Peter Pan is real), sociology,</p><p style="text-align: center;">and other cultural subject to explain the truth about society.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Called himself an "Award winning filmmaker" with a recent prize at the "Social Uprising Grassroot and Resistance"filmfestival in the US. Film was a private release (to avoid censorship) ca/Jed "Ivory Heart".</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">He believes Canberra is the occult capital of the World.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He thinks the Freemasons are a satanic cult that sacrifice children and that the Grandmaster is in Canberra. He is investigating them, documenting them and has proof to show others eg police of their crimes and he wants to take over the Freemasons to save everyone from them.</p><p style="text-align: center;">There is no person he has speclfically identified, still looking, but states he has all the evidence.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He described a bizzare belief in a ritual that the Freemason's do including sucking the blood from an artery to use the effects of substances from the ?adrenal gland {?for power/health)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">He believes that Artificial Intelligence (Al) is taking over the world. That Al has integrated into all our technology and creating synthetic bodies to appear as humans.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â· Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Wenda/lÂ·showedÂ·usÂ·a-video-{partof0Â·Â·wentfor45Â·minsÂ·"-weÂ·watchedÂ·about-5Â·mins)Â·Â·heÂ·createdÂ·on-his-iphone-Â·Â·Â·Â·Â· titled "War games" as proof of this.</p><p style="text-align: center;">It was an amateur footage of trees and a Canberra building with a voice over that didn't make much sense, but</p><p style="text-align: center;">then footage of another phone with a Siri-type animation lady answering his questions about the Freemasons. (Answered seemed auto-generated from a siri-like assistant program, but Wendall was adamant this was an example of Ai's capabilities and manevolent intent..)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendall believes he is now the head of the 1//uminati, who use to be an organisation intent on taking over the world as well but he stopped this. Hence his focus now on the Freemasons and Al.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendall also read a long email he sent to to the AFP yesterday detailing his beliefs that the Freemasons have infiltrated them, and his proof of the Freemasons evil and that they should act etc. Although the sentence structure was logical, his ideas were difficult to follow at times included a reference to a "pineal gland addiction" and mentioning "atrocities" without defining them.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Also described on a mission looking for his wife that he reference some attachment {?spiritually) at birth and it is his quest to find her. Tattoo on chest was a name he has given her but yet to find her real name. Also showed various tattoos that had religious or other special significance in his various quests.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I tried to explore with Wendell any past psychiatric treatment/experiences.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">He states he has been "imprisoned" in Canberra, Grafton and 1-2 other psychiatric hospitals in Australia. He believes this was due to trying to censor him. Adamant he has never had mental health problems.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He has had olanzapine in the past and found it awful, very sedating/flattening and felt it was done with malevolent intent.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He states risperidone was "even worse" but didn't give specifics as started to get irritable about me watching to</p><p style="text-align: center;">push medications on him.</p><p style="text-align: center;">11Hates"seroquel.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Won't consider anything new eg Abilify as does not believe he needs it and thinks we are pushing medication to censor him or for some other ill intent or for our benefit/gain.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Only medication he would accept is "Xanax" for when he felt he need to rest/slow down. Explained rarely</p><p style="text-align: center;">prescribed now and why. Seemed to accept this and did not push for script.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">D&A</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell denies any i/lict drug use eg cannabis, Ice, ecstacy, synthetics.</p><p style="text-align: center;">However he states he buys "herbs" from the chemist and smokes those sometimes. Nil alcohol.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Nicotine stains noted on fingers.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Medical</p><p style="text-align: center;">nil medical history of note disclosed states he is "very healthy, fit and strong" nil physical complaints/concerns</p><p style="text-align: center;">Agrees he hasn't had blood tests for a long time, and agreeable to have some done. Agreeable to finding a GP</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Family:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell wasn't keen to talk about this family. He states his parents are in USA.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He has not contacted them for years as they do not believe in what he is doing. Same with his "one biological brother Ricky"</p><p style="text-align: center;">Also states his parents adopted 27-31 children around the world.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·Â·Â· ......_Friends,..................- ........ -----</p><p style="text-align: center;">states he has a few close friends but did not want to elaborate.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Risk:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell is intent on finding the Freemasons, and confronting people if he suspects that are them or to tell them his views about needing to be warned/saved. He agreed some people won't listen to him but that hehad to try. There was no single person he had identified yet in his "evidence".... "I don't know yet... I amÂ  still looking".</p><p style="text-align: center;">He would like to challenge the grandmaster in "hand to hand combat" but "no way would I kill/hurt him... I am</p><p style="text-align: center;">a pacifist.... I just want to be the new leader of the Freemasons... like I did with the Illuminati" His proof of leadership of the Illuminati was not from a combat challenge but an email he sent to a "princess" which he showed us and didn't make much sense (and I noted email address had rebounded as undelivered}</p><p style="text-align: center;">He denies any thought or intent to hurt someone even if he felt, for example, they had sacrificed children. He denied any problems with police and has never been aggressive/threatened people.</p><p style="text-align: center;">He was upset that I asked about this as it went against his ethics/morals.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell's biggest current risk is potentially aggravating others with his driven beliefs and conflict arising. Misadventure from his homelessness and living in a tent in a harsh approaching winter could be a problem.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">There is also the past risk incident when he inserted a speaker wire into his penis (2013} and the possibility of further incidents if based on a delusional belief.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Chronic risks for Wendell is a poor prognosis and recovery the longer a psychotic illness is left untreated, that any medical contributors to his psychosis have yet to be investigated, and that he likely to stay unemployed, itinerant and on the fringe.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">It is unknown if he would ever act violently based on his delusions. There is not enough past known history try and quantitate risk other than his psychotic illness is a risk factor.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Seems to have a degree of organisation eg with newstart, streetwise about food/gear, does not look too dishevelled.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mental State Examination including dates conducted:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Excerpt for mental health nurse assessment note Karina Boyd 1st June 2018:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell was much more elevated and grandiose this morning. He stated he had not slept last night, had very little food (breath smelt slightly of acetone) and was "feeling fantastic" and was "loving the world". He was animated and demonstrative when showing author the actions of an incident he stated he had been involved in earlier in the week.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Speech: rapid rate, expressive tone, normal volume. Difficult to keep up with his conversation due to Wendell jumping from topk to topic. Difficult for author to respond during interaction due to the pressure of speech. Affect: Elevated, grandiose, appears to be de-compensating with mental health. Congruent with stated mood. Thought Content:</p><p style="text-align: center;">He has had many ideas to help the world with producing and videotaping his "teaching modules" for open learning. ''As a film maker I have to produce. I have produced 12 -15 hours of the course. It is a 21 episode course made up of 15 - 20 minutes modules."</p><p style="text-align: center;">Stated he had "challenged the Freemasons to send their best warrior" and the next day "a guy who was a gang</p><p style="text-align: center;">===/,Â  el'!k=c e=mmed=W-emkf/=#-epej=JeFehe,Jd=i# i,,-s====j=</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·Â  Â·-Â·-noted)Â·butÂ·the person received-the head butt andfee/toÂ·the ground,Â·Â·Wendell reportsÂ·he was-with 2 Â·other</p><p style="text-align: center;">males. He reported this incident to the AFP (Simone) and has not pressed charges. He states in the next few weeks "I will be grand master" (Freemasons).</p><p style="text-align: center;">He is convinced Canberra is the "occult capital of the world". I am now taking over the leadership of the Freemasons.</p><p style="text-align: center;">"I am leader of the 11/uminati<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>it took me 4 years from 2011 - 2015."</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mental State Examination from Psychiatry Assessment Dr C Flynn 1st June 2018:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Casually dressed, reasonably tidy, mid-length wavy long brown hair almost to shoulders, skinny build but did not look malnourished. Pale complexion</p><p style="text-align: center;">Multiple small tattoos, reasonable quality, with elaborate meanings linked to his belief systems. Many seemed</p><p style="text-align: center;">to be in ancient writing/languages.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Alert, orientated. Came across as very intelligent with use of language, vocabulary range.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Cooperative, started and finished interview very polite, pleasant, calling me "mam" because "I am polite and say that to everyone". However more irritable and driven during interview when talking about his beliefs, and became quite angry (but contained) talking about past imprisonment, conspiracies, being censored etc.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Irritable about past mental health treatment.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Speech- pace changed when more driven/irritable to increased rate, but could be interrupted. Raised volume when more driven, otherwise normal volume.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Affect- reactive, congruent with content. Periods of being irritable/cranky but containable and other times pleasant and polite. General ernest, trying to impress to us the importance of his beliefs and action needed.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Thought form - logical sentence structure and generally could follow linkages with his ideas (Videos and emails were not as easy to follow)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Thought content- as described. Lots of delusions with themes of conspiracies, being censored, world</p><p style="text-align: center;">takeover/invasion, Apocalypse being here etc. Grandiosity, likely grandiose delusions. eg no evidence that he has produced a high quality film award winning film, as amateur one poor, but could be a past truth of sorts.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 7 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Religious themes/references.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">No insight into having a mental illness, rather that it is other people who are unwell if they don't believe his proof, evidence etc. Will not trial any medication as he believes he is well and that any medication for his mental health is medical doctors trying to censor him or for some other ill intent or for our benefit/gain</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Relevant Past History</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith has only had two prior contact periods with our Service.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The first was in April 2012, referred by GP, resulting in a short involuntary PSU (acute adult psychiatric ward) admission, Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The referral from GP stated "He presented to me with some magical thinking, no auditory hallucinations; he has no friends and claimed to be Jiving on the mountain. There is a family history of schizoid personality disorder. I believe he has schizotypal personality disorder."</p><p style="text-align: center;">He was seen by CATT clinicians, with Mr Nesmith agreeable to coming to hospital for an assessment but he had told CATT "that our system will not help; that this is the #2 in a psychiatric ward; your doctors will diagnose me as either schizophrenia or schizotypal; they will force medication on me and push their own ideal of what a</p><p style="text-align: center;">.1,,wen..,;eesHmefu5APt!ldd;,"f-,bwill..he-!;<epffiffi55@0'!;..t./JNQÂ  'Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>bi,</p><p style="text-align: center;">ignored-andstigmaswi/1 be-pushed-on-me;-doctors-will-misjudge-what-theysee-infront-ofthem-andcategorise--Â­ me; your systems do not help BUT/ no longer care about anything so the follies of your society will have to deal with its creation: ME OR I end my life. Your choice. I no longer care."</p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith was assessed by a psychiatrist Dr J Cubis who thought he had a likely psychotic illness or schizotypal personality disorder. Mr Nesmith was admitted to PSU (acute adult mental health unit) on 28th April - 5th May 2012.Â  Mr Nesmith did not talk or cooperate much with the admission and as he was not floridly psychotic, the team could not uphold a PTO, so he was discharged and lost contact with services.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The second contact was brief in 2013 by the psychiatry C/L Canberra Hospital team after a bizarre incident where he had inserted<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>speaker wire into his penis requiring surgical intervention. Surgical team referred to psychiatry C/L as his speech was hard to follow, he had odd behaviours/beliefs, and seemed quite paranoid. He was initially placed on an ED7 as presented psychotic with thought disorder and grandiose. But this was taken off a few days later as he presented more settled with no evidence of psychosis, though his odd and eccentric personality, paranoid themes and alternate lifestyle (camping in bushland near Mt Ainslie to avoid people) was noted at the time. He was hence discharged, and not seen again by our services until this year.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">When asked about this hospital incident ri=cently Mr Nesmith talked about being "embarrassed" it had happened and that it was "sexual experimentation" that went horribly wrong, as he wanting to try and "increase sexual stimulation".</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In regards to other psychiatric presentations, Mr Nesmith has spoken about being "locked up" in hospitals in various places in NSW, at least on 2 occasions, with him believing he was being "censored" for his beliefs and part of a greater conspiracy and cover-up. He was reluctant to give details of his time in hospital or precise locations. He could list by name several antipsychotics used (olanzapine, risperidone, quetiapine) and the awful side effects experienced, adding to his negative experience. It does not seem he has ever taken</p><p style="text-align: center;">anti psychotics long-term, only in restrictive environments.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">There is no known history of his earlier years in the US before he moved to Australia. He states he is estranged from his US parents and siblings because they "don't believe in my cause". He is adamant he does not want contact with them. We have not found any longer-term friend or contact for any collateral history alas.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">DECISION-MAKING CAPACITY</p><p style="text-align: center;">5. Does the person, or can the person (with assistance if needed):</p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) Understand when a decision about treatment, care or support needs to be made?</p><p style="text-align: center;">?Yes<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>IBl No</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(b) Understand the facts that relate to the decision?</p><p style="text-align: center;">(c) Understand the main choices?</p><p style="text-align: center;">(d) Weigh up the consequences of the main choices?</p><p style="text-align: center;">(e) Understand how the consequences affect the person?</p><p style="text-align: center;">(f) On the basis of (a)-(e) make the decision?</p><p style="text-align: center;">(g) Communicate the decision in whatever way the person can?</p><p style="text-align: center;">IBl Yes</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">? Yes</p><p style="text-align: center;">IBl Yes</p><p style="text-align: center;">?Yes</p><p style="text-align: center;">?Yes</p><p style="text-align: center;">?Yes</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">?No</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">IBl No</p><p style="text-align: center;">? No</p><p style="text-align: center;">IBl No IBl No IBl No</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Describe and explain your overall assessment referring to the factors above and to the principles of decision-making capacity set out in section 8 (see Glossary):</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith does not believe his has a mental illness, and that anyone who questions his beliefs or</p><p style="text-align: center;">--- intentions.is part.of.the wide-spread.censorship and.cover-ups ...He..also.believes..medica.1 staff enforce.. their own views of societal norms and illness in a biased way and with ill-intent. Any discussion of mental illness or offer of antipsychotic medication is seen as us being judgemental, dismissive, and at worse, part of the conspiracy to keep him from doing his tasks of saving humanity from various threats. He has a hint of insight than he can get "busy" and elevated, but only wants "Xanax" (alprazolam) to help slow him down. He believes this is part of his excitable personality style and not a sign of a mood or psychotic disorder. The notion of going to hospital for treatment is also seen as the ultimate punishment alas, and he would find this very traumatic and coercive and further proof of the medical establishments malevolence. This belief is also based on real past negative experiences with involuntary psychiatric admissions and side effects from several anti psychotics that he reports.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">REFUSAL</p><p style="text-align: center;">6. Does the person refuse to receive treatment, care or support; or, if the person has decision-making</p><p style="text-align: center;">capacity, refuse to consent to treatment, care or support?</p><p style="text-align: center;">IBJYes<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>? No</p><p style="text-align: center;">If yes, describe what the person does and/or says that constitutes refusal</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith is refusing to trial any antipsychotic medication due to his conviction that he does not have a mental illness and that any treatment will be unjust, unfounded and cause harm.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">RISK OR DETERIORATION (answer on basis of likelihood if untreated)</p><p style="text-align: center;">7. Is the person doing, or likely to do serious harm to themselves or someone else because of the mental</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">illness or mental disorder?<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>IBlYes ? No</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Is the person suffering, or likely to suffer serious mental or physical deterioration because of the mental illness or mental disorder?<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>IBJYes<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>? No</p><p style="text-align: center;">If yes, explain your reasons for this opinion.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Risk prediction is a fraught area as clinicians cannot be precise or quantitate risk given the variables and unpredictable nature of people's behaviour and their environments.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">However, the risks to Mr Nesmith include that the longer he is left with an untreated psychotic illness the worse his prognosis and quality of recovery, that could have devastating impacts on his ability to work, have relationships, live and function in society. There is a potential risk of him falsely identifying a community member as the "grandmaster" of the Freemasons based on a delusion, and conflict arising with possible violent sequelae although there is no past history of violent altercations yet that we know of. His intinerant and secretive lifestyle limits any corroborative history. He may be at risk of angering others with his "investigations" and misadventure. There are risks around camping in the bush regions if he was to have physical health issues or not have enough gear for w rmth. Personal safety and security is also problematic.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Is is not known if Mr Nesmith would self-harm if he became overwhelmed by his predicament and fate</p><p style="text-align: center;">of the world. There was the past incident of inserting a wire into his penis which may have been due</p><p style="text-align: center;">=======reea"leevviel-ef-=Fei'FE!ffi5'â‚¬lilsl.'Fgifftf!1'8l'ffli-laattitefffiF'Efelm;ielFf mil'Fat-4e4i;;;eofwire-4ttsei-Eill'ff======l= liunikelygiven h7smental sfateÂ·postcoperationrana hence Â·p-ossil51effuturFriskofotlier suchrisky</p><p style="text-align: center;">incidents to self.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">TREATMENT</p><p style="text-align: center;">8. What treatment, care or support is proposed? (If a treatment plan is prepared it may be attached to this form)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">It is unlikely, given his lack of insight that Mr Nesmith would agree to trial an oral anti psychotic in the community and be adherent. Hence a treatment trial would involve a hospital environment with the goals of starting an oral antipsychotic eg paliperidone or aripiprazole and switching to a depot preparation. Several weeks would be required and the inpatient setting choices include the Acute Adult Mental Health Unit at Canberra Hospital or possibly a rehabilitation facility that may be less stressful for him.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Community follow-up would include regular contact with a case-manager and doctor, psychological therapy if desired, and assistance linking to services for housing and other goals he may have in his recovery eg further study or work.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">9, Why or how will treatment care or support be Hkely to reduce harm, or deterioration, or result in an improvement to the person's condition?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">It is hoped that Mr Nesmith's delusional preoccupations are reversible, and that with treatment he would be able to not be so consumed in saving the world, collect evidence, confronting organisations etc and transfer his intellect and creativity to other pursuits that hopefully provide joy, fulfillment and security and not place him at risk. The risks associated with chronic mental illness would hopefully be reduced and his quality of life improved. There is a possibility that he is estranged from his US family due to delusional beliefs and this could potentially be healed and increase his supports.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">10. Why can't the treatment ca _c,r upport .: a_eq_ a,e y prov1 e w1<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>es r of choice and movement of the person?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Primarily because Mr Nesmith will not consent to treatment in the community setting and is likely to disengage from our services entirely if he feels we are a threat to his liberty. Any reasonable treatment trial will involve at least 4-8 weeks of adequate dose medication.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr Emma Glanville</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr Emma Glanville</p><p style="text-align: center;">MBBS MP FRANZCP</p><p style="text-align: center;">Consultant Psychiatrist City Mental Health</p><p style="text-align: center;">1 Moore Street Canberra ACT 2601</p><p style="text-align: center;">Ph; (02) 62051338- Provider No, 236841 NY</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Full name of Applicant (relevant official or delegate or nominee of the Chief Psychiatrist)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Date: 19/06/2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 11 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">GLOSSARY</p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 10 Meaning of mental if/ness</p><p style="text-align: center;">In this Act:</p><p style="text-align: center;">mental illness means a condition that seriously impairs (either temporarily or permanently) the mental functioning of a person inl or more areas of thought, mood, volition, perception, orientation or memory, and is characterised by-</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) the presence ofat least 1 of the following symptoms:</p><p style="text-align: center;">(i) delusions;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(ii) hallucinations;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(iii) serious disorders of streams of thought;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(iv) serious disorders of thought form;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(v) serious disturbance of mood; or</p><p style="text-align: center;">(b) sustained or repeated irrational behaviour that may be taken to indicate the presence of at least 1 of the symptoms mentioned in paragraph (a).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 9 Meaning of mental disorder</p><p style="text-align: center;">In this Act:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 12 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">mental disorder-</p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) means a disturbance or defect, to a substantially disabling degree, of perceptual inteqiretation, comprehension, reasoning, learning, judgment, memory, motivation or emotion; but</p><p style="text-align: center;">(b) does not include a condition that is a mental illness.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 7 Meaning of decision-making capacity</p><p style="text-align: center;">For this Act, a person has capacity to make a decision in relation to the person's treatment, care or support for a mental disorder or mental illness (decision-making capacity) if the person can, with assistance if needed-</p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) understand when a decision about treatment, care or support for the person needs to be made; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">(b) understand the facts that relate to the decision; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">(c) understand the main choices available to the person in relation to the decision; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">(d) weigh up the consequences of the main choices; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">(e) understand how the consequences affect the person; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">(f) on the basis of paragraphs (a) to (e), make the decision; and</p><p style="text-align: center;">(g) communicate the decision in whatever way the person can.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Section 8 Principles of decision-making capacity</p><p style="text-align: center;">(1) In considering a person's decision-malcing capacity under this Act, the following principles must be taken into account:</p><p style="text-align: center;">a a persons ec1s1on-m ang capac1 1 p<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>u<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>o<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>1 1 n</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â·Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>(ii) a person must be assumed to have decision-malcing capacity, unless it is established that theÂ­</p><p style="text-align: center;">person does not have decision-making capacity;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(c) a person who does not have decision-making capacity must always be supported to make decisions about the person's treatment, care or support to the best of the person's ability;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(d) a person must not be treated as not having decision-making capacity unless all practicable steps to assist the person to make decisions have been taken;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(e) a person must not be treated as not having decision-making capacity only becauseÂ­</p><p style="text-align: center;">(i) the person malces an unwise decision; or</p><p style="text-align: center;">(ii) the person has impaired decision-making capacity under another Act, or in relation to another decision;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(f) a person must not be treated as having decision-malcing capacity to consent to the provision of treatment, care or support only because the person complies with the provision of the treatment, care or support;</p><p style="text-align: center;">(g) a person who moves between having and not having decision-making capacity must, if reasonably practicable, be given the opportunity to consider matters requiring a decision at a time when the person has decision-making capacity.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(2) A person's decision-making capacity must always be talcen into account in deciding treatment, care or support, unless this Act expressly provides otherwise.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(3) An act done, or decision made, under this Act for a person who does not have decision-malcing capacity must be done in the person's best interests.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(4) In considering a person's decision-malcing capacity under this Act, any approved code of practice under section 198 must be taken into account.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Page 13 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">IN THE AUSTRALIAN CAPITAL TERRITORY CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">In respect of WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH</p><p style="text-align: center;">D.O.B. 27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Tribunal:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Presidential Member M-T Daniel Senior Member L Drew</p><p style="text-align: center;">Member R Davies</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Date of Order:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>2 August 2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PSYCHIATRIC TREATMENT ORDER</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Tribunal Orders:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">1. The Tribunal makes a Psychiatric Treatment Order in relation to Wendell Charles Nesmith.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">2. Wendell Charles Nesmith must comply with any determination made by the Chief Psychiatrist or delegate under section 62 of the Mental Health Act 2015.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">3. Unless sooner revoked, this order has effect for 6 months.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Tribunal notes:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) This order will be reviewed on its own motion prior to expiry.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">STATEMENT</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(i)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(ii)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">This statement sets out how Wendell Charles Nesmith meets the criteria for a psychiatric treatment order under section 58(2) of the Mental Health Act 2015. The findings in the statement are based on the information before the Tribunal and are made on the balance of probabilities.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles Nesmith has a mental illness because he has a condition that seriously impairs (either temporarily or permanently) his mentalÂ  ctioning in</p><p style="text-align: center;">areas incl ding !hought nd moodhich s characterised}1)\he\F'pr, e ce of symptoms including delusions and serious disturbance of moqdÂ  Â .Â  ' ,9,</p><p style="text-align: center;">IÂ·, ..' 3--â€¢Â  â€¢</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">_r.,. â€¢<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>$ ...#:;_?.) -,J</p><p style="text-align: center;">(iii) Wendell Charles Nesmith does not have decision-making/ capacity to, c6r:isertt\ o the treatment, care or support because he cannot undersf?rid wlf .n<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>n about his treatment, care or support needs to be made (t \( eci !Ql'.1);<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>ot weigh up the consequ nces of the main choices; he ca dt, Q_de; a tf the consequences affect him; and he cannot make the dec1s1on o f,ba 1 of the matters set out above.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(iv) Wendell Charles Nesmith refuses the treatment determined in relation to himself because although he says he will accept treatment and in the very recent past has been accepting treatment; he has a 7 year history of ceasing treatment after advising health authorities he will continue with treatment. The Tribunal considers his current compliance with treatment is of a short duration and against the extensive history is of the view that he refuses treatment.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(v) The Tribunal believes on reasonable grounds that because of his mental illness, Wendell Charles Nesmith is likely to do serious harm to himself as a result of misadventure or self neglect when unwell.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(vi) The Tribunal believes on reasonable grounds that because of his mental illness, Wendell Charles Nesmith is likely to suffer serious deterioration of his mental state and functioning if untreated.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(vii) The Tribunal is satisfied that psychiatric treatment, care or support is likely to reduce the likelihood of harm or deterioration mentioned above and is likely to result in an improvement in Wendell Charles Nesmith's psychiatric condition.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(viii) The Tribunal is satisfied that the treatment, care or support to be provided under tt,e psychiatric treatment order cannot be adequately provided in another way that would involve less restriction of Wendell Charles Nesmith's freedom of choice</p><p style="text-align: center;">',;?V</p><p style="text-align: center;">1r\o-]J.</p><p style="text-align: center;">-<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>--<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>!</p><p style="text-align: center;">Presi entir,-1 M<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>er M-T Daniel</p><p style="text-align: center;">-</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">â€¢ ACT CIVIL AND ADMINISTRATIVE TRIBUNAL</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Our Ref:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>MH 108/2012</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">WENDELL CHARLES NESMITH</p><p style="text-align: center;">C/- Tribunal Liaison, Psychiatric Unit, The Canberra Hospital Building 25, Yamba Drive</p><p style="text-align: center;">GARRAN ACT 2605</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-a