her)]</p><p style="text-align: center;">Note if the affidavit extends over more than I page, the person making the affidavit and the person taking the affidavit must sign or initial each page of the affidavit (seer 6715 (I) (Affidavit-taking of)).</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">*omit if, or whichever is, inapplicable</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">AF2007-72<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Form 6.11-Affidavit-genera\<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>page2</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Belconnen Mental Health Team</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Canberra Health Services</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Belconnen Community Health Centre</p><p style="text-align: center;">, 56 Lathlain St, Belconnen</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Phone: (02) 6205 1110</p><p style="text-align: center;">Fax:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>(02) 6205 0988</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">29th November 2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">RE: Wendell Charles Nesmith<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>DOB: 27/06/1984</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dear Wendell,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">As you are aware you are on Psychiatric Treatment Order which requires to follow treatment advice/reccomentations to better your mental well-being and quality of life. I am happy to discuss treatment options with you achieve your goals. To facilitate this we need your utmost co-operation. This includes following the treatment advice that we agree on. I wish to monitor metabolic risk factors and serum levels of Olanzapine, to assist gradual transition from depot Olanzapine to oral Olanzapine. I also request you not to do any video recording without seeking permission from the person you are recording.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">I hope get favourable response from you to this letter. I am looking forward to having collaborative discussions regarding your treatments and clinical needs.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">thanking you, Regards,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>urali Reddy Consultant Psychiatrist</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 1 of 1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Form 5.4<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Supreme Court-notice of appeal</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Court Procedures Rules 2006</p><p style="text-align: center;">(seer 5100 (Appeals to Supreme Court-starting appeal))</p><p style="text-align: center;">In the Supreme Court of the Australian Capital Territory</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">No SCA<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>of2019</p><p style="text-align: center;">On appeal from ACT Civil and Administrative Tribunal (AA42 of2018 and MH 108 of2012)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles NeSmith</p><p style="text-align: center;">Appellant</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Chief Psychiatrist</p><p style="text-align: center;">Respondent</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">1. On 19 November 2018, the ACT Civil and Administrative Tribunal made the following order:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Psychiatric (The decision of the Tribunal on 2 August 2018 to make a psychiatric treatment order is confirmed)</p><p style="text-align: center;">2. The appellant appeals from all the order.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if appeal.from only part of order, state the part appealed.from)</p><p style="text-align: center;">3. The appellant will seek to put further evidence before the Court.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if further evidence is sought to be put before the Court, state briefly the nature of the evidence and what is sought to be proved)</p><p style="text-align: center;">I have both writings and video footage that occurred at and around the time of the order and these are being ignored. In addition, my</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Filed for the appellant Wendell Charles NeSmith, XXXXXX</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">AF2006-388<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Approved form under Court Procedures Act 2004, s 8</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">page 1</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">website is being ignored. In addition, my human rights were severely violated when my lawyer quit the last appeal.</p><p style="text-align: center;">5. The grounds of the appeal are:</p><p style="text-align: center;">I was NOT a risk to myself or anyone else at the time the order was made (or at any other time in my life). I was merely protesting one of Centrelink's terrible procedures which I would do again if the same thing happened.</p><p style="text-align: center;">6. The orders sought are:</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â  Â  Â  Remove psychiatric order. Bring justice to those who violated my human rights including all of those who chose to ignore real evidence.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if r 5101 (3) applies)</p><p style="text-align: center;">7. *[The appellant wants to present the appellant's case in writing and video.]</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if the appellant is represented by a solicitor)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">*Particulars of appellant's solicitor</p><p style="text-align: center;">Solicitor's full name: My lawyer in the ACAT case quit, which is a huge human rights issue that ACAT did NOT care about a single bit. I need a real lawyer that is not going to quit at a difficult case.</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if the solicitor practises in afirm of solicitors)</p><p style="text-align: center;">*Solicitor's firm: Legal Aid Solicitor's full business address: TBA Solicitor's telephone no: TBA</p><p style="text-align: center;">*Name, address and telephone no of solicitor's agent: TBA</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Appellant's address for service of documents</p><p style="text-align: center;">(set out appellant's address for service) nesmith.net (Rebirthing)</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if represented by a solicitor the following information may be given)</p><p style="text-align: center;">*Document exchange box no:</p><p style="text-align: center;">(if postal address different from address for service)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-ali