 seems less driven than prior to</p><p style="text-align: center;">25<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>hospitalisation. Very grandiose, no insight that he has a psychotic illness, is agreeing have farther treatment because of fears of further torture, e.g. going back to hospital. Engagement will continue to be fraught with this tension but currently was able to establish good rapport today. The ongoing plan - continue</p><p style="text-align: center;">30<span style="white-space: pre;">		</span>Olanzapine depo, consider dose increase (indistinct) arrange new GP at the interchange.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">So you need a new GP?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">35<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>MR NESMITH: Yes; but they won't take new patients right now.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PRESIDENT MEMBER DANIEL: The interchange practice?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MR SHORT:Â  Yes.</p><p style="text-align: center;">40</p><p style="text-align: center;">PRESIDENT MEMBER DANIEL: "Needs to start process ofDSP". I think that's disability support pension?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Housing support, need to explore all emergency temporary housing</p><p style="text-align: center;">45<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>options. Centre/ink certificate dated until mid-October.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">.MHIOS/12 02.08.18<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>P-6</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Diagnosis schizophrenia. See scanned copy. Case manager to look into psychological and other support.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;