d</p><p style="text-align: center;">25<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Mr Nesmith?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MR NESMITH: The only reason that I stopped taking my medication is because I went to the US and the medication was $600 per month there and I could not afford $600 per month for the medication. I would have stayed on it</p><p style="text-align: center;">30<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>if it was not for that.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MEMBER DAVIES: So these notes do say that in 2016 that you went to the US but in front of me here I've got a psych history that says you were treated with Risperidone in Ballarat in - - -</p><p style="text-align: center;">35</p><p style="text-align: center;">MR NESMITH: Risperidone is bad. No.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MEMBER DAVIES: Canberra in 2013, Lismore 2014 with Olanzapine and that you didn't like those medications.</p><p style="text-align: center;">40</p><p style="text-align: center;">MR NESMITH: I don't like Risperidone at all.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MEMBER DAVIES: In fact, you have, there is at page 47, I'm just pointing out that there is precedents here where you have stopped taking medications in</p><p style="text-align: center;">45<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>the past.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">MR NESMITH: I went from Risperidone to Olanzapine.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PRESIDENT MEMBER DANIEL: Okay. Where did you go to be prescribed</p><p style="text-align: center;">5<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>the Olanzapine? Was that still in Queensland?</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: 