one poor, but could be a past truth of sorts,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created l3y: Pr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;">Printed By: Dr Caroline Hynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Paga 7 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Rellg/ous themes/references.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">No Insight Into having a mental illness, rather that it Is other people who are unwell If they don't believe his proof, evidence etc. WIii not trial any medlcotion as he belleves he Is well and that any medication for his mental health is medical doctors trying'to censor him or forsome other ill intent or for our benefit/gain</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Relevant Past History</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Mr Nesmith has only had two prior contact periods with our Service.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The first was In April 2012, referred by GP, resulting In a short involuntary PSU (acute adult psychiatric ward) admission, Canberra Hospital</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The referral from GP stated "I-le presented to me with some mag/ca/ thinking;no auditory hallucinations; he has no friends and claimed to be living on the mountain. There Is a family history of schizoid personality disorder. I believe he has sch/zotypa/ personality disorder."</p><p style="text-align: center;">He was seen by CATT clinicians, with Mr Nesmith agreeable to coming to hospital for an as.sessment but he had</p><p style="text-align: center;">told CATT "that