allperldone or arlplprazole and switching to a depot preparation. Several weeks would be required and the Inpatient setting choices Include the Acute Adult Mental Health Unit at Canberra Hospital or possibly a rehabilitat1on facility that may be less stressful for him.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">...-....<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>-Â·</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Created By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar) Printed By: Dr Caroline Flynn (Registrar)</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Page 10 of 14</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Community follow-up would Include regular contact with a case-manager and doctor, psychological therapy If desired, and assistance linking to services for housing and other goals he may have In his recovery eg further study or work.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">9, Why or how will treatment care or support be likely to reduce harm, or deterioration, or result in an Improvement to the person's condltloni'</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">It Is hoped thut Mr Nesmlth's delusional preoccupations are reversible, and that with treatment he would be able to not be so consumed In saving the world, collect evidence, confronting organisations etc and transfer his Intellect and creativity to other pursuits that hopefully provide Joy, fulfillment and. security and not place him at risk. The risks associated with chronic mental Illness would hopefully be reduced and his quality of life Improved. There Is a possibility that he Is estranged from his US family</p><p style="text-align: center;">due to delusional beliefs and this could potentially be healed and Increase his supports.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">10, WhY. can't the treatment care or support f5e adequafoly prov1aedWlcfflilss r sMdlo11 al ElieÂ  l,eed6111</p><p style="text-align: center;">ofch lce nd movement oTth Â·pers;r;:iÂ·Â·Â·Â·Â·-Â·-Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·Â·-Â·Â· Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>............,-.......<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Â·â€¢Â  -</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Primarily because Mr Nesmith wlll not consent to treatment in the community setting and Is likely to disengage from our services entirely If he feels we are a threat to his liberty, Any reasonable treatment trial wilt Involve at least 4-8 weeks of adequate dose medication,</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr Emma Glanville</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Dr Emma Glanville</p><p style="text-align: center;">MBBS MP FRANZCP</p><p style="text-align: center;">Consultant Psychiatri