/p><p style="text-align: center;">Pate of Order:<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>2 August 2018</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">PSYCHIATRIC TREATMENT ORDER</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Tribunal Orders:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">1. The Tribunal makes a Psychiatric Treatment Orde_r in relation to Wendell Charles Nesmith.</p><p style="text-align: center;">2. Wendell Charles Nesmith must comply With any determination made by the Chief Psychiatrist or delegate under section 62 of the Mental Health Act 2015.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">3. Unless sooner revoked, this order has effect for 6 months.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">The Tribunal notes:</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(a) This order will be reviewed on its own motion prior to expiry.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">STATEMENT</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(i) This statement sets out how Wendell Charles Nesmith meets the criteria for a psychiatric treatment order under section 58(2) of the Mental Health Act 2015.</p><p style="text-align: center;">The findings in the siatemeht are based on the information before the Tribunal</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">and are made on the balance of probabilities.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">.., c\-,Â·Â·1\ f117/J'/""','"-,,,,</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â£-;}, '<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>' l<>"'-'</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(iii</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">Wendell Charles Nesmith has a mental illness because he has .; dcmditJth that ,</p><p style="text-align: center;">se_riou ly impa.irs (either temporarily Cl:. pe:manently) Is menal/f4i.);i Xifn_m1 areas including thought and mood which 1s characterised by ae }F,lf!_lJ: .\J;i, 'J 'f _:,</p><p style="text-align: center;">symptoms including delusions and serious disturbance of mood.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(iii) Wendell Charles Nesmith does not have decision-making capaci -- } f?,\ll\ P\11?fl' the treatment, care or support because he cannot understand whenÂ·a derns1on about his treatment, care or support needs to be made (the decision); he cannot weigh up the consequences of th!" main choices; he cannot understand how the consE>qUE>nces ciffect him; and he cannot make the decision on the basis of the matters set out above.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(iv) Wendell Charles Nesmith refuses the treatment determined in relation to himself because although he says he will accept treatment and in the very recent past has been accepting treatment; he has a 7 year history of ceasing treatment afterÂ· advising health authorities he will continue with trec1tment. The Tribunal considers his current compliance with treatment is of a short duration and against the extensive history is of the view that he refuses treatment.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">(v) The Tribunal believes on reasonable grounds that because of his mental illness, Wendell Charles Nesmith is likely to do serious harm to himself as a result of misadventure or self neglect when unwell.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: