ear to authorto have an active plan. Reports mood as "great"; affect reactive. Using good eye contact.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Settled behaviour; participating in art group.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Refusing to speak with treating team still. Very unhappy that the doctors would not communicate with him unless he is able to write. Appears quite fearful of the mental health system, has likely had negative experiences in Victoria.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Believes if he speaks he won't be listened to anyway and his words will be taken out of context. Afraid of being given injections against his will, does not want any medications or</p><p style="text-align: center;">.think these are necessary. ?Personality disorder traits becoming observable.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Transferred to LOU room P11 at lunch time.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">New</p><p style="text-align: center;">lss ues/Exceptions</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p style="text-align: center;">: A.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>. Nilroutine niedicat1ons charted.Given hospital paj.,mos,</p><p style="text-align: center;">. cls!on tow ls nd soap; enco!Jfi!ged.to.haveashm,yer; Clothes washed: Has been tai<ing y()ghurt and juices.â€¢.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Â· .observati'oi:is taken as charted, .<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>_Â· Â·Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>. Â· _Â·Â· ..<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Â·. Â·<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>.</p><p style="text-align: center;">Enco4raged to speak with_ welfare officer Judy lvloore re, :</p><p style="text-align: center;">Centrelink payments, has declined to do so.<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>. .</p><p style="text-align: center;">R<span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Settled in LDU; orientated to new environment.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><br /></p><p 